WEBVTT

1
00:01:47.375 --> 00:01:48.834
Move! Move!

2
00:01:48.918 --> 00:01:50.542
Make way! Make way!

3
00:02:26.251 --> 00:02:28.834
Hey! Let me see your hands!

4
00:02:53.709 --> 00:02:55.626
Jesus Christ. that's Hermann Göring.

5
00:02:55.709 --> 00:02:57.709
- Who?
- Hitler's second-in-command.

6
00:02:58.959 --> 00:03:00.043
The <i>Führer-</i>in-waiting.

7
00:03:12.043 --> 00:03:13.043
What did he say?

8
00:03:14.542 --> 00:03:16.626
He asked us to get his luggage.

9
00:03:36.793 --> 00:03:37.876
Justice Jackson?

10
00:03:38.959 --> 00:03:40.626
That depends on if you have a good reason

11
00:03:40.709 --> 00:03:42.793
to be banging on my door
at 3:00 in the morning.

12
00:03:42.876 --> 00:03:44.584
They captured Hermann Göring alive.

13
00:03:46.793 --> 00:03:48.126
-Where?
-Austria.

14
00:03:50.918 --> 00:03:52.001
What are they gonna do with him?

15
00:03:52.084 --> 00:03:54.417
Well. that's the real question.
isn't it? Can I come in?

16
00:03:54.501 --> 00:03:56.459
-No.
-But it's raining.

17
00:03:56.542 --> 00:03:59.168
I can see that. Are they gonna shoot him?

18
00:03:59.251 --> 00:04:00.375
Not that I know of.

19
00:04:01.667 --> 00:04:03.459
Well. for a long time.
they were gonna shoot him.

20
00:04:03.542 --> 00:04:04.542
Yes. sir.

21
00:04:04.626 --> 00:04:06.501
Churchill and Roosevelt
signed the order themselves.

22
00:04:06.583 --> 00:04:07.709
An order you opposed.

23
00:04:07.793 --> 00:04:09.334
I'm a Supreme Court Justice.

24
00:04:09.416 --> 00:04:11.918
I tend to frown on executing men
without a trial.

25
00:04:12.001 --> 00:04:13.542
That's what I'm here to talk about.

26
00:04:15.793 --> 00:04:16.793
<i>It can't be done.</i>

27
00:04:16.876 --> 00:04:19.375
- You keep saying that.
- Because it can't be done.

28
00:04:19.459 --> 00:04:20.751
Give me one good reason why not.

29
00:04:20.834 --> 00:04:23.085
There's no legal precedent for a trial.

30
00:04:24.334 --> 00:04:26.751
There's no international law
to base the charges on.

31
00:04:26.834 --> 00:04:30.834
No one has ever tried war criminals
outside of one nation's jurisdiction

32
00:04:30.918 --> 00:04:33.667
because the whole concept
of international law is that

33
00:04:33.751 --> 00:04:36.834
one country can't tell another country's
citizens how to conduct themselves.

34
00:04:36.918 --> 00:04:38.793
-Elsie...
-Trying these men

35
00:04:38.876 --> 00:04:40.584
in a German court would be different.

36
00:04:40.667 --> 00:04:42.542
But what you're talking about
is trying them

37
00:04:42.626 --> 00:04:45.043
in some sort of legal limbo
that doesn't exist.

38
00:04:45.126 --> 00:04:47.417
using case law
that hasn't been written yet.

39
00:04:47.501 --> 00:04:49.667
and on the off chance
that you're not keeping track.

40
00:04:49.751 --> 00:04:51.584
that's about four good reasons why not.

41
00:04:51.667 --> 00:04:54.168
- I'm getting you a drink.
- I don't want a drink.

42
00:04:54.251 --> 00:04:56.584
Then I'm getting me another
and getting you one for show.

43
00:04:57.626 --> 00:04:58.876
Who do you put on trial?

44
00:05:00.834 --> 00:05:02.168
The German commanders?

45
00:05:02.918 --> 00:05:04.376
Enlisted men?

46
00:05:04.459 --> 00:05:06.793
What about the judges
who enforced the racial codes?

47
00:05:06.876 --> 00:05:08.667
Obviously. we'd have to work that out.

48
00:05:08.751 --> 00:05:12.501
And once you decide who to put on trial.
what do you charge them with?

49
00:05:13.459 --> 00:05:16.251
Conspiracy to wage
aggressive war on the world.

50
00:05:16.334 --> 00:05:20.334
And you want the United States
to argue that as the prosecution?

51
00:05:20.417 --> 00:05:21.751
I do.

52
00:05:21.834 --> 00:05:23.501
Against Germany.

53
00:05:23.584 --> 00:05:26.001
a country that never attacked us.

54
00:05:29.126 --> 00:05:31.501
-Say. just for a second. it could be done.
-Robert...

55
00:05:31.584 --> 00:05:32.918
Don't you wanna know how I'd do it?

56
00:05:34.334 --> 00:05:38.334
It would have to be
a completely international effort.

57
00:05:40.376 --> 00:05:43.126
<i>All of the Allies
would have to participate.</i>

58
00:05:43.210 --> 00:05:44.293
<i>The U.S..</i>

59
00:05:44.376 --> 00:05:47.126
<i>Britain. France. Russia.</i>

60
00:05:47.210 --> 00:05:49.501
<i>You can't do it without the Russians.</i>

61
00:05:49.584 --> 00:05:51.876
<i>Four international judges.</i>

62
00:05:51.959 --> 00:05:53.793
<i>You're talking about a tribunal.</i>

63
00:05:53.876 --> 00:05:54.876
<i>Exactly.</i>

64
00:05:55.417 --> 00:05:58.210
<i>The world needs to know
what these men did.</i>

65
00:05:58.793 --> 00:06:00.293
It's a logistical nightmare.

66
00:06:00.376 --> 00:06:01.376
I know.

67
00:06:03.542 --> 00:06:05.168
But it has to be done.

68
00:06:36.293 --> 00:06:37.501
Pick a card.

69
00:06:39.668 --> 00:06:40.668
I don't think so.

70
00:06:45.626 --> 00:06:46.834
Ask me to pick one.

71
00:06:57.542 --> 00:06:58.542
Pick a card.

72
00:07:06.168 --> 00:07:09.001
Now ask me to please remember it
and put it back in the deck.

73
00:07:10.376 --> 00:07:13.210
Please remember it
and put it back in the deck.

74
00:07:17.252 --> 00:07:18.501
Now shuffle 'em.

75
00:07:29.085 --> 00:07:30.293
Now what?

76
00:07:30.376 --> 00:07:32.043
My card was the three of spades.

77
00:07:32.126 --> 00:07:33.334
Well. that's hardly a trick.

78
00:07:33.417 --> 00:07:34.543
Turn over the top one.

79
00:07:47.793 --> 00:07:48.793
Who are you?

80
00:07:49.918 --> 00:07:51.043
I'm a psychiatrist.

81
00:07:53.376 --> 00:07:55.709
Oh. and why are you going to Mondorf?

82
00:07:55.793 --> 00:07:56.834
I wish I knew.

83
00:07:58.168 --> 00:08:00.501
They send psychiatrists
on secret missions now?

84
00:08:00.584 --> 00:08:02.334
I'm pretty sure I'm the first.

85
00:08:06.793 --> 00:08:09.834
How did you do that? With the cards.

86
00:08:10.751 --> 00:08:12.043
I didn't do anything.

87
00:08:13.835 --> 00:08:15.960
You're a really good magician.

88
00:08:30.001 --> 00:08:31.501
Dr. Kelley?

89
00:08:31.583 --> 00:08:33.252
Sergeant Howie Triest. at your service.

90
00:08:33.334 --> 00:08:35.626
I'm gonna run you over
to the commandant's office.

91
00:08:35.709 --> 00:08:37.417
-Tigers. huh?
-Yes. sir.

92
00:08:37.501 --> 00:08:38.960
Perhaps I'll see you around.

93
00:08:41.626 --> 00:08:42.626
Jiminy.

94
00:08:43.626 --> 00:08:45.043
Who was that?

95
00:08:45.126 --> 00:08:47.334
That. Howie. was a very attractive woman.

96
00:08:47.417 --> 00:08:49.501
Did you say "commandant"?

97
00:08:50.668 --> 00:08:51.835
Uh. yes. sir. Colonel Andrus.

98
00:08:53.210 --> 00:08:55.626
So. can you tell me
what I'm supposed to be doing here?

99
00:08:55.709 --> 00:08:57.334
I thought the war was over.

100
00:08:58.334 --> 00:08:59.543
I couldn't say.

101
00:09:00.543 --> 00:09:01.960
Couldn't say because you don't know

102
00:09:02.043 --> 00:09:04.127
or you couldn't say 'cause somebody
told you you couldn't say?

103
00:09:05.751 --> 00:09:07.043
I couldn't say.

104
00:09:07.626 --> 00:09:08.709
Hmm.

105
00:09:09.376 --> 00:09:11.543
Don't get sore at me. Doc.
I'm just your translator.

106
00:09:12.376 --> 00:09:13.626
Translator for what?

107
00:09:15.293 --> 00:09:17.334
You'll see.

108
00:09:23.918 --> 00:09:26.918
<i>Dr. Kelley. apparently.
Central Command thinks</i>

109
00:09:27.001 --> 00:09:29.252
<i>you're some kind of hotshot headshrinker.</i>

110
00:09:29.334 --> 00:09:31.085
<i>I imagine you have some questions for me.</i>

111
00:09:31.168 --> 00:09:33.168
-More than a few.
-Then let's get to it.

112
00:09:33.252 --> 00:09:36.043
You are standing inside
a secret military prison.

113
00:09:36.127 --> 00:09:38.918
It currently houses what's left
of the Nazi High Command.

114
00:09:39.001 --> 00:09:42.793
The governments of Russia. France.
Great Britain. and our United States

115
00:09:42.876 --> 00:09:46.751
are deciding right now whether to put
these men on trial for their lives.

116
00:09:46.835 --> 00:09:50.001
You have been brought in
to inspect and ensure

117
00:09:50.085 --> 00:09:53.043
the prisoners' mental health
should that trial go forward.

118
00:09:53.626 --> 00:09:54.960
Suicide.

119
00:09:55.043 --> 00:09:57.459
That'll be the main concern
with most of the prisoners.

120
00:09:57.543 --> 00:10:01.001
Hitler. Goebbels. and Himmler
have already taken their own lives.

121
00:10:01.085 --> 00:10:02.876
We cannot afford any more losses.

122
00:10:04.043 --> 00:10:05.918
Goebbels and Himmler did it with this.

123
00:10:07.210 --> 00:10:08.793
Hidden cyanide capsule.

124
00:10:09.751 --> 00:10:11.668
The one you'll have to watch
the closest is Göring.

125
00:10:12.252 --> 00:10:13.252
Göring?

126
00:10:14.418 --> 00:10:15.459
As in Hermann Göring?

127
00:10:15.543 --> 00:10:16.626
That's the one.

128
00:10:17.710 --> 00:10:18.793
Hermann Göring's here?

129
00:10:19.543 --> 00:10:22.001
Sergeant. is it possible
the major suffered a large blow

130
00:10:22.085 --> 00:10:23.293
to his head on the way to my office?

131
00:10:23.376 --> 00:10:25.334
- Not that I'm aware of. sir.
- Sorry.

132
00:10:25.418 --> 00:10:28.001
-It's just a lot to process.
-Sure it is. Try and do it faster.

133
00:10:28.085 --> 00:10:29.668
-Yes. sir.
-When Göring surrendered.

134
00:10:29.751 --> 00:10:31.626
he was traveling with his family.

135
00:10:31.710 --> 00:10:34.459
He had over a million dollars
in German currency and jewelry.

136
00:10:34.543 --> 00:10:36.085
And a large quantity...

137
00:10:36.168 --> 00:10:37.626
...of these.

138
00:10:37.710 --> 00:10:39.960
We had them sent back
to the States for classification.

139
00:10:41.584 --> 00:10:42.584
Paracodeine.

140
00:10:43.210 --> 00:10:45.459
Fairly potent painkiller. I'm a fan.

141
00:10:47.043 --> 00:10:48.127
He says they're for his heart.

142
00:10:48.210 --> 00:10:52.293
Well. then. I have a rather large bridge
in Brooklyn to sell you.

143
00:10:52.376 --> 00:10:54.626
These have nothing to do with the heart.
They're an opiate.

144
00:10:55.668 --> 00:10:57.668
How many pills does he take a day?

145
00:10:57.751 --> 00:10:59.334
-Sergeant?
-Forty. sir.

146
00:11:00.710 --> 00:11:03.751
I think it's safe to say
the <i>Reichsmarschall's</i> got a drug problem.

147
00:11:04.543 --> 00:11:05.626
Where's his family now?

148
00:11:05.710 --> 00:11:07.710
They've been released
and they're not your concern.

149
00:11:07.793 --> 00:11:11.543
Your only job is to evaluate
Göring and the others. That is it.

150
00:11:12.668 --> 00:11:14.085
Sir. I'm a good doctor.

151
00:11:14.168 --> 00:11:19.127
but the entire Nazi High Command might be
a little bit beyond my area of expertise.

152
00:11:19.210 --> 00:11:21.710
Believe me. Major. this was not my idea.

153
00:11:23.210 --> 00:11:24.210
Dismissed.

154
00:11:28.085 --> 00:11:30.252
He's not great at pep talks. is he?

155
00:11:30.334 --> 00:11:32.293
Commandant's not known
for his warmth. sir.

156
00:11:32.376 --> 00:11:34.210
-I wanna meet him.
-Who?

157
00:11:34.293 --> 00:11:36.002
-Göring. Right now.
-Excuse me. sir.

158
00:11:36.085 --> 00:11:37.252
You don't wanna get settled first?

159
00:11:37.334 --> 00:11:39.294
I wanna know what I'm dealing with.

160
00:11:39.376 --> 00:11:40.751
All right. well. don't be too intimidated.

161
00:11:40.835 --> 00:11:42.210
I'm not. Tell me about him.

162
00:11:43.127 --> 00:11:46.294
<i>Reichsmarschall</i> Hermann Göring.
President of the <i>Reichstag.</i>

163
00:11:46.376 --> 00:11:49.835
Minister of Aviation.
Commander-in-Chief of the <i>Luftwaffe.</i>

164
00:11:49.918 --> 00:11:54.085
Minister of Economics. a founding member
of the <i>Gestapo</i> secret police.

165
00:11:54.168 --> 00:11:56.584
was appointed Hitler's successor in 1939

166
00:11:56.668 --> 00:11:59.127
and is the highest ranking
German military officer of all time.

167
00:11:59.210 --> 00:12:00.210
Okay.

168
00:12:00.918 --> 00:12:02.835
Now I'm a little intimidated.

169
00:12:02.918 --> 00:12:03.960
Don't be. You're good.

170
00:12:04.960 --> 00:12:07.793
<i>Reichsmarschall.</i>

171
00:12:07.876 --> 00:12:09.252
<i>Guten Tag. Herr Triest.</i>

172
00:12:12.334 --> 00:12:14.710
<i>Reichsmarschall</i> Göring.
my name is Dr. Douglas Kelley.

173
00:12:20.085 --> 00:12:21.668
He says. "Wonderful. a doctor."

174
00:12:21.751 --> 00:12:23.501
I am. May I take your pulse?

175
00:12:26.168 --> 00:12:27.793
<i>Ja. ja.</i>

176
00:12:31.334 --> 00:12:33.043
He's been asking
for his pills.

177
00:12:33.127 --> 00:12:34.960
- He wants you to get 'em for him.
- Mm-hmm.

178
00:12:35.043 --> 00:12:37.043
I understand you've had heart trouble.

179
00:12:42.710 --> 00:12:44.168
"I've had
several minor heart attacks

180
00:12:44.252 --> 00:12:45.793
"and the pills help with that."

181
00:12:45.876 --> 00:12:47.418
Can you open your shirt. please?

182
00:12:51.876 --> 00:12:53.252
Mm-hmm.

183
00:12:55.127 --> 00:12:58.210
Respiration is rapid
and shallow. Don't translate that.

184
00:13:00.043 --> 00:13:02.710
The pills help with the pain as well?

185
00:13:04.751 --> 00:13:05.918
<i>Ja. ja.</i>

186
00:13:10.418 --> 00:13:12.459
He says he was
shot down in World War I.

187
00:13:12.543 --> 00:13:13.835
He has a bullet in his right hip.

188
00:13:13.918 --> 00:13:17.294
In 1923. he was shot in the groin

189
00:13:17.376 --> 00:13:18.459
during the Munich Putsch.

190
00:13:18.543 --> 00:13:19.751
You've been shot a lot. sir.

191
00:13:24.501 --> 00:13:26.418
"Occupational hazard."

192
00:13:26.835 --> 00:13:29.334
Well. if you really
wanna look after your heart.

193
00:13:29.418 --> 00:13:31.710
the best way to do that
is to lose some weight.

194
00:13:41.877 --> 00:13:43.252
"I assure you. you are looking

195
00:13:43.334 --> 00:13:45.127
"at the best physique in all of Germany.

196
00:13:45.210 --> 00:13:46.501
"just ask my wife."

197
00:13:47.085 --> 00:13:50.169
I'm sure you're right. sir.
but the guards here call you "Fat Stuff."

198
00:13:54.793 --> 00:13:55.793
I'm sure...

199
00:13:56.585 --> 00:14:00.085
it would be difficult for a lesser man
to lose this weight.

200
00:14:00.169 --> 00:14:05.210
but you possess a fortitude and discipline
that others do not. yes?

201
00:14:12.169 --> 00:14:13.501
"You see. this man is different."

202
00:14:17.252 --> 00:14:19.459
"We're gonna
be good friends. I'm sure of it."

203
00:14:20.918 --> 00:14:22.376
I look forward to that.

204
00:14:23.960 --> 00:14:25.668
- Good day.
<i>- Auf Wiedersehen.</i>

205
00:14:32.501 --> 00:14:34.127
Inflated sense of self.

206
00:14:35.334 --> 00:14:36.334
Charming.

207
00:14:37.418 --> 00:14:38.501
Speaks English.

208
00:14:39.835 --> 00:14:41.501
What? What? What?

209
00:14:41.585 --> 00:14:44.002
Yeah. the way he looked at me
when I called him fat.

210
00:14:44.085 --> 00:14:46.085
Yeah. he understood me.
He's been playing you.

211
00:14:48.585 --> 00:14:50.710
No. No. why... why would he pretend?

212
00:14:50.793 --> 00:14:53.668
Translation gives him more time
to consider his answers.

213
00:14:53.751 --> 00:14:55.585
He thinks that gives him an advantage.

214
00:14:57.543 --> 00:14:59.127
Wait. hold on.

215
00:14:59.710 --> 00:15:01.751
You're saying I spent
the last three months

216
00:15:01.835 --> 00:15:03.793
mumbling to myself
while he understood every word?

217
00:15:03.877 --> 00:15:04.877
Pretty much.

218
00:15:05.877 --> 00:15:06.877
Jiminy.

219
00:15:07.585 --> 00:15:09.460
Are you... Are you gonna tell him
that you know?

220
00:15:09.543 --> 00:15:12.252
No. no.
No. he's gonna tell me when he's ready.

221
00:15:13.127 --> 00:15:15.877
-When's that?
-When he determines I'm not a threat.

222
00:15:17.334 --> 00:15:19.252
I wanna meet the rest of 'em. Who's next?

223
00:15:19.376 --> 00:15:22.376
Uh... Dr. Robert Ley.

224
00:15:23.418 --> 00:15:25.418
- Chief of the German Labor Front.
- Mmm-hmm.

225
00:15:25.501 --> 00:15:27.169
One of Hitler's earliest followers.

226
00:15:27.960 --> 00:15:30.169
<i>He once wrote a book that was
so complimentary of the</i> Führer

227
00:15:30.252 --> 00:15:32.918
<i>that Hitler had the entire run destroyed
'cause he was so embarrassed.</i>

228
00:15:34.918 --> 00:15:38.127
<i>Ley. who spearheaded
the Nazi slave labor program</i>

229
00:15:38.210 --> 00:15:39.918
<i>was captured in his pajamas.</i>

230
00:15:40.002 --> 00:15:42.418
<i>calling himself "Dr. Distelmeyer."</i>

231
00:15:47.543 --> 00:15:49.793
"I'm not
like these other power-hungry men

232
00:15:49.877 --> 00:15:51.085
"you have locked up in here."

233
00:15:55.626 --> 00:15:57.127
"I can smell the Jew."

234
00:15:59.877 --> 00:16:01.710
<i>Great Admiral Karl Dönitz.</i>

235
00:16:01.793 --> 00:16:04.002
<i>The German Navy's Commander-in-Chief.</i>

236
00:16:04.085 --> 00:16:06.752
<i>Architect of the U-boat attacks
that crippled the British Navy.</i>

237
00:16:08.210 --> 00:16:11.418
<i>Dönitz condoned
murder of prisoners on the high seas.</i>

238
00:16:12.835 --> 00:16:15.543
<i>A fanatical Nazi.
with the arrest of Dönitz.</i>

239
00:16:15.626 --> 00:16:17.835
<i>the Third Reich is ended forever.</i>

240
00:16:21.210 --> 00:16:23.626
"I have been
in custody for 76 days.

241
00:16:23.710 --> 00:16:27.210
"I have yet to be formally arrested
or charged with a specific crime.

242
00:16:27.294 --> 00:16:30.626
"which is a direct violation
of the Geneva Conventions.

243
00:16:30.710 --> 00:16:32.460
"Charge me or release me."

244
00:16:33.668 --> 00:16:36.918
<i>Julius Streicher.
Hitler's Director of Propaganda.</i>

245
00:16:37.002 --> 00:16:38.835
<i>Publisher of the national
anti-Semitic paper.</i>

246
00:16:38.918 --> 00:16:39.960
Der Stürmer.

247
00:16:40.044 --> 00:16:41.044
<i>Streicher!</i>

248
00:16:41.127 --> 00:16:45.294
<i>Dubbed the high priest of anti-Semitism
and the Beast of Franconia.</i>

249
00:16:45.376 --> 00:16:48.752
<i>led the Jewish boycott...

250
00:16:48.835 --> 00:16:52.044
<i>...and ruled Nuremberg
with an iron fist.</i>

251
00:16:54.585 --> 00:16:55.960
He wants to know
if you're a Jew.

252
00:16:56.626 --> 00:16:57.835
No.

253
00:17:01.334 --> 00:17:02.918
"But you work
in a Jewish profession."

254
00:17:10.668 --> 00:17:12.501
"What do you fight for. Doctor?"

255
00:17:15.335 --> 00:17:18.044
<i>Göring is the key.</i>

256
00:17:18.126 --> 00:17:21.585
<i>The leader of a nation in exile.
He binds them all together.</i>

257
00:17:22.793 --> 00:17:26.668
<i>He's begun a strict self-imposed
diet and exercise regimen.</i>

258
00:17:26.752 --> 00:17:29.085
<i>and is going cold turkey on the pills.</i>

259
00:17:29.793 --> 00:17:32.418
<i>It's almost as if
he's training for something.</i>

260
00:17:33.294 --> 00:17:35.418
<i>If one were to write a book
about him. it...</i>

261
00:17:48.335 --> 00:17:49.960
Is there a library in town?

262
00:17:50.044 --> 00:17:52.085
- You wanna go to a library?
- Yes.

263
00:17:52.752 --> 00:17:54.877
- At 2:33 in the morning?
- Yes. Get your coat.

264
00:17:57.585 --> 00:17:58.585
I'll get my coat.

265
00:18:00.752 --> 00:18:03.752
The sheer amount of narcissists
we got locked up in that hotel.

266
00:18:03.835 --> 00:18:06.002
I bet at least half have books in here

267
00:18:06.085 --> 00:18:08.752
written about them or written by them.

268
00:18:08.835 --> 00:18:10.793
We're gonna figure these guys out.

269
00:18:10.877 --> 00:18:13.376
Oh. yeah?
You speak a lot of German. Doc?

270
00:18:14.376 --> 00:18:16.127
Not even a little.
How'd you learn?

271
00:18:16.210 --> 00:18:20.169
My mother spoke German
and I wanted to be like her.

272
00:18:22.169 --> 00:18:23.627
You really think you can do it?

273
00:18:23.710 --> 00:18:24.793
Do what?

274
00:18:25.793 --> 00:18:28.752
Well. get these guys to open up to you.

275
00:18:28.835 --> 00:18:29.835
Sure.

276
00:18:31.543 --> 00:18:32.543
How?

277
00:18:34.460 --> 00:18:37.211
Everybody wants to be listened to.
It's a natural instinct.

278
00:18:38.543 --> 00:18:41.501
I learn about them.
I get them to trust me.

279
00:18:42.627 --> 00:18:43.627
They open up.

280
00:18:44.835 --> 00:18:46.211
Make it sound so easy.

281
00:18:47.252 --> 00:18:49.085
What if we could dissect evil?

282
00:18:49.960 --> 00:18:52.627
I mean. what sets these men
apart from all the others?

283
00:18:52.710 --> 00:18:55.376
What enabled them
to commit the crimes that they did?

284
00:18:55.960 --> 00:18:57.501
They almost took over the world.

285
00:18:58.335 --> 00:19:00.294
You've heard
about the work camps for Jews?

286
00:19:04.169 --> 00:19:06.835
Rumor has it they weren't just work camps.

287
00:19:08.294 --> 00:19:09.294
I've heard.

288
00:19:10.044 --> 00:19:12.335
So. how do people become like that?

289
00:19:12.418 --> 00:19:14.919
We actually have a shot
to figure that out.

290
00:19:16.211 --> 00:19:20.710
To find out
what makes the Germans different.

291
00:19:21.585 --> 00:19:22.585
Different?

292
00:19:24.376 --> 00:19:25.376
From us.

293
00:19:27.294 --> 00:19:29.835
A man who writes a book about that
could make a lot of money.

294
00:19:34.793 --> 00:19:37.127
You know. for a second.
I thought you were being noble.

295
00:19:39.668 --> 00:19:40.710
You want noble?

296
00:19:42.668 --> 00:19:43.668
Fine.

297
00:19:43.752 --> 00:19:47.543
If we could psychologically define "evil."

298
00:19:49.044 --> 00:19:52.211
we could make sure something like this
never happens again.

299
00:20:06.127 --> 00:20:08.169
- What's going on?
- Hermann Göring can't breathe.

300
00:20:09.668 --> 00:20:11.418
- Move!
- Howie!

301
00:20:17.960 --> 00:20:18.960
<i>Herr.</i>

302
00:20:19.044 --> 00:20:20.794
- Okay. his airway is clear.
- That's good. right?

303
00:20:20.877 --> 00:20:21.960
No. he's having a heart attack.

304
00:20:22.044 --> 00:20:23.044
- What?
- Where the hell's

305
00:20:23.127 --> 00:20:24.294
- the prison doctor?
- He's on his way.

306
00:20:24.376 --> 00:20:25.376
All right. Tell him to hurry.

307
00:20:25.460 --> 00:20:26.710
-Howie. I need some aspirin.
-Yeah.

308
00:20:26.794 --> 00:20:28.002
- Plain old ordinary aspirin.
- Got it! Got it!

309
00:20:28.085 --> 00:20:29.585
Get it now! Go! Hey. hey. hey.

310
00:20:29.668 --> 00:20:32.376
Your heart's still beating.
which means you're alive.

311
00:20:32.460 --> 00:20:34.085
I'm gonna keep you that way. okay?

312
00:20:34.169 --> 00:20:35.919
I need you to stay calm. all right?

313
00:20:36.002 --> 00:20:39.710
Breathe with me. In and out. In and out.

314
00:20:40.418 --> 00:20:42.294
I'm here. I'm here. Look at me. I'm here.

315
00:20:42.376 --> 00:20:44.002
I'm not gonna let you die. all right?

316
00:20:44.710 --> 00:20:46.044
In and...

317
00:20:48.127 --> 00:20:49.877
Here. Is that your wife?

318
00:20:50.543 --> 00:20:53.211
She's here. She's here. She's here.

319
00:20:53.294 --> 00:20:54.376
Breathe. Breathe with me.

320
00:20:54.460 --> 00:20:55.877
Doc's on his way.
Doc's on the way. Aspirin.

321
00:20:55.960 --> 00:20:58.502
Yeah. Hand me a few of those.
will ya? Thank you. Howie.

322
00:20:58.585 --> 00:21:00.919
Hey. hey. best thing for the heart.

323
00:21:01.002 --> 00:21:02.543
plain old aspirin. Yeah.

324
00:21:05.086 --> 00:21:06.127
Mmm... Mmm...

325
00:21:06.627 --> 00:21:09.127
Trust me. all right?

326
00:21:09.211 --> 00:21:10.960
Breathe.
In and out. Mm-hmm.

327
00:21:11.044 --> 00:21:13.627
Chew. chew. Yeah. Better.

328
00:21:13.710 --> 00:21:16.543
Yeah. your pulse is slow. Yeah.

329
00:21:16.627 --> 00:21:20.502
Hey. guess what?
You're alive. You're alive.

330
00:21:21.169 --> 00:21:22.169
Well. how about that?

331
00:21:23.252 --> 00:21:24.252
Thank you.

332
00:21:24.335 --> 00:21:26.294
Let's get him to the infirmary.
Come on.

333
00:21:37.960 --> 00:21:39.127
What're you smiling for?

334
00:21:39.543 --> 00:21:40.543
Hmm?

335
00:21:42.668 --> 00:21:44.211
He said "thank you" in English.

336
00:21:49.585 --> 00:21:52.294
Truman wants to win re-election in '48.

337
00:21:52.377 --> 00:21:55.668
He's not gonna do that coddling the Nazis.

338
00:21:55.752 --> 00:21:56.877
True enough.

339
00:21:56.960 --> 00:22:01.377
Plus. a trial means giving them a chance
to tell their stories to the world.

340
00:22:01.460 --> 00:22:03.252
What are we afraid to hear them tell?

341
00:22:03.752 --> 00:22:06.252
We won the damn war. Bob.

342
00:22:06.335 --> 00:22:10.543
If you do this. it'll turn into
the biggest boondoggle of all time.

343
00:22:10.627 --> 00:22:13.377
-Cameras in the damn courtroom...
-And what if they're sympathetic?

344
00:22:13.460 --> 00:22:16.127
What if all this does
is provide them with a platform

345
00:22:16.211 --> 00:22:18.086
for anti-Semitism all over the world?

346
00:22:18.794 --> 00:22:20.543
You wanna be responsible for that?

347
00:22:22.710 --> 00:22:24.960
You wanna know if I'm comfortable

348
00:22:25.044 --> 00:22:28.335
executing a few Nazis without a trial?

349
00:22:28.418 --> 00:22:29.710
Damn right. I am.

350
00:22:32.127 --> 00:22:33.627
It doesn't matter anyway.

351
00:22:34.377 --> 00:22:35.669
You'll never get the Russians.

352
00:22:37.502 --> 00:22:39.294
We got the Russians.

353
00:22:39.377 --> 00:22:41.460
- What?
- We got the Russians.

354
00:22:42.252 --> 00:22:43.294
We did?

355
00:22:43.377 --> 00:22:45.211
Truman called Stalin himself.

356
00:22:45.294 --> 00:22:47.460
Looking at Nikitchenko
for lead prosecutor.

357
00:22:47.543 --> 00:22:48.877
That's fantastic news.

358
00:22:48.961 --> 00:22:50.418
I have no idea who you are.

359
00:22:51.211 --> 00:22:53.669
Colonel John Amen. sir.
I work for the Judge Advocate General.

360
00:22:55.002 --> 00:22:57.794
So. the Army sent us a lawyer?

361
00:22:58.543 --> 00:22:59.543
Yes. sir.

362
00:22:59.627 --> 00:23:02.627
I bring greetings from General Eisenhower.
who says he wants you to know

363
00:23:02.710 --> 00:23:04.752
that he's not for hanging anyone
without a trial.

364
00:23:04.835 --> 00:23:06.211
Well. that's progress.

365
00:23:06.294 --> 00:23:08.169
He also says he hopes
the trial won't take too long

366
00:23:08.252 --> 00:23:09.710
so we can get on with hanging them.

367
00:23:09.794 --> 00:23:12.086
Hmm. Have a seat.

368
00:23:13.961 --> 00:23:15.794
I've read a lot about you. sir.

369
00:23:15.877 --> 00:23:17.460
They say you're gonna be
the next Chief Justice.

370
00:23:17.543 --> 00:23:19.669
President promised him
the seat personally.

371
00:23:19.752 --> 00:23:21.335
And swore me to secrecy.

372
00:23:21.418 --> 00:23:25.211
so let's maybe not tell everyone
who walks into the office about it. okay?

373
00:23:25.294 --> 00:23:28.294
Well. everyone in my office says
there's no way you get the trial.

374
00:23:29.169 --> 00:23:30.169
What do you say?

375
00:23:31.253 --> 00:23:32.585
I say I like an underdog.

376
00:23:33.835 --> 00:23:35.211
Good morning. Julius.

377
00:23:36.002 --> 00:23:39.377
I'm gonna show you a series of cards.
each with inkblots.

378
00:23:39.460 --> 00:23:42.460
and you're gonna tell me
what each inkblot makes you see.

379
00:23:43.794 --> 00:23:46.919
Perhaps it will
reveal something about your character.

380
00:23:47.002 --> 00:23:49.794
your intelligence. creativity.

381
00:23:49.877 --> 00:23:52.086
And everything here stays between us.

382
00:23:56.961 --> 00:23:57.961
<i>Herr Doktor.</i>

383
00:23:59.418 --> 00:24:00.418
Yes.

384
00:24:01.627 --> 00:24:05.585
I can speak to you in English
if it is of some help.

385
00:24:07.752 --> 00:24:09.418
Only if it makes you comfortable.

386
00:24:10.502 --> 00:24:11.502
Shall we begin?

387
00:24:12.294 --> 00:24:14.169
"Butterfly."

388
00:24:14.253 --> 00:24:16.211
"Witch."

389
00:24:18.418 --> 00:24:19.627
"Torpedo hit."

390
00:24:19.710 --> 00:24:21.502
Somebody has spilled something.

391
00:24:23.127 --> 00:24:25.086
I see 10.000 horses.

392
00:24:25.710 --> 00:24:29.002
I see the Valkyries ride.

393
00:24:32.294 --> 00:24:33.294
"A vagina."

394
00:24:34.502 --> 00:24:35.794
"A vagina."

395
00:24:39.961 --> 00:24:41.418
"A Jewish vagina."

396
00:24:41.502 --> 00:24:42.710
Huh.

397
00:24:42.794 --> 00:24:44.002
This is blood.

398
00:24:44.086 --> 00:24:45.294
Whose blood?

399
00:24:48.169 --> 00:24:49.253
Or ink.

400
00:24:49.794 --> 00:24:51.710
You can say a lot of things with ink.

401
00:24:53.502 --> 00:24:55.836
<i>I'm sorry. Bob. Word came down tonight.</i>

402
00:24:55.919 --> 00:24:57.127
<i>It's gonna be a no.</i>

403
00:24:57.211 --> 00:24:58.211
Mmm.

404
00:24:59.794 --> 00:25:02.418
Congress is going to say no to the trial.

405
00:25:02.502 --> 00:25:04.294
They just want executions.

406
00:25:05.544 --> 00:25:07.169
-I'm out of moves.
-What about the President?

407
00:25:07.253 --> 00:25:10.377
President wants someone to hide behind.
that's why he needs Congress.

408
00:25:11.418 --> 00:25:13.294
Neither will do it without the other.

409
00:25:13.377 --> 00:25:16.169
- So you need someone bigger to back it.
- Oh. come on.

410
00:25:16.253 --> 00:25:17.919
Who's bigger than the President?

411
00:25:32.585 --> 00:25:34.335
Jesus Christ.

412
00:25:35.377 --> 00:25:36.377
Literally.

413
00:25:37.544 --> 00:25:39.585
-Are you a Catholic?
-I am now.

414
00:25:42.627 --> 00:25:44.294
The Holy Father will see you now.

415
00:25:44.377 --> 00:25:45.377
Hmm.

416
00:25:46.877 --> 00:25:50.544
You wish to put these men
on trial for their lives.

417
00:25:50.627 --> 00:25:53.877
and you have come to ask
for the Church's blessing in this.

418
00:25:55.002 --> 00:25:59.086
Your support would go a long way
to building an international consensus.

419
00:25:59.169 --> 00:26:01.169
No one denies these men are evil.

420
00:26:02.460 --> 00:26:03.919
But an eye for an eye...

421
00:26:05.460 --> 00:26:06.544
is not the answer.

422
00:26:06.627 --> 00:26:09.710
Maybe not. but I'm pretty sure
where I first read about it.

423
00:26:13.211 --> 00:26:14.335
Are you Catholic?

424
00:26:15.002 --> 00:26:16.002
No. sir.

425
00:26:17.377 --> 00:26:18.585
A religious man?

426
00:26:19.544 --> 00:26:20.585
Not especially.

427
00:26:20.669 --> 00:26:24.211
And yet. at home. they call you a Justice.

428
00:26:24.294 --> 00:26:25.627
I didn't pick the name.

429
00:26:25.710 --> 00:26:28.502
If you sit long enough
in judgement of others.

430
00:26:29.211 --> 00:26:34.086
you come to believe the laws of man
outweigh the laws of God.

431
00:26:36.335 --> 00:26:37.669
I don't believe that.

432
00:26:37.752 --> 00:26:38.919
Then...

433
00:26:41.002 --> 00:26:42.253
what do you believe?

434
00:26:45.128 --> 00:26:46.669
I believe in man.

435
00:26:46.752 --> 00:26:51.044
In our capacity to save ourselves
from men like the Nazis.

436
00:26:52.460 --> 00:26:54.335
I believe this to be a good act.

437
00:26:54.419 --> 00:26:57.836
One so good you must circumnavigate
your own laws to achieve it?

438
00:26:59.836 --> 00:27:04.335
I'm sorry. but the Catholic Church
cannot support you in this.

439
00:27:08.919 --> 00:27:11.377
But you could support them in 1933.

440
00:27:14.836 --> 00:27:16.128
I'm sorry?

441
00:27:16.961 --> 00:27:19.961
You signed the Concordat
with Hitler yourself.

442
00:27:21.711 --> 00:27:23.544
That was a different matter.

443
00:27:23.627 --> 00:27:27.169
You lived in Munich.
you were the nuncio to the German Empire.

444
00:27:27.253 --> 00:27:30.169
The Catholic Church
was the first world power

445
00:27:31.086 --> 00:27:33.086
to acknowledge the <i>Führer</i> State.

446
00:27:33.585 --> 00:27:35.335
You gave the Nazis credibility.

447
00:27:35.419 --> 00:27:37.836
In order to protect Catholics in Germany.

448
00:27:37.919 --> 00:27:42.711
Isn't it a pity the Jews
didn't have someone to do that for them?

449
00:27:44.169 --> 00:27:46.128
Do you think I condone what they did?

450
00:27:51.128 --> 00:27:52.961
People will remember. sir...

451
00:27:55.335 --> 00:27:57.711
what you did in 1933.

452
00:27:59.044 --> 00:28:00.585
what you do now.

453
00:28:01.627 --> 00:28:03.128
<i>They'll tell their children.</i>

454
00:28:05.711 --> 00:28:08.836
Did the Catholic Church
stand with the Nazis...

455
00:28:10.752 --> 00:28:12.044
or against them?

456
00:28:18.169 --> 00:28:19.794
Did you just blackmail the Pope?

457
00:28:19.877 --> 00:28:21.627
I don't wanna talk about it.

458
00:28:24.877 --> 00:28:26.752
Word came down last night.

459
00:28:27.377 --> 00:28:28.669
There's gonna be a trial.

460
00:28:32.836 --> 00:28:33.877
A trial?

461
00:28:36.044 --> 00:28:38.169
Good. Good.

462
00:28:39.211 --> 00:28:40.669
As it should be.

463
00:28:49.961 --> 00:28:52.335
Those cards that you showed me.

464
00:28:53.419 --> 00:28:55.377
what did they teach you about me?

465
00:28:56.877 --> 00:28:59.211
Honestly. that you are highly intelligent.

466
00:28:59.295 --> 00:29:00.460
Ah...

467
00:29:00.544 --> 00:29:02.335
I could have told you this.

468
00:29:02.419 --> 00:29:04.711
And that you're a narcissist

469
00:29:04.794 --> 00:29:08.711
given to an expansive
and aggressive fantasy life.

470
00:29:08.794 --> 00:29:12.460
with a strong ambition and drive
to subjugate the world

471
00:29:12.544 --> 00:29:15.044
as you find it
to your own pattern of thinking.

472
00:29:17.044 --> 00:29:18.711
And you were surprised by this?

473
00:29:20.169 --> 00:29:21.169
No.

474
00:29:21.919 --> 00:29:24.711
Then the cards have taught you nothing.

475
00:29:26.086 --> 00:29:29.044
<i>Herr</i> Triest. he tells me you do magic.

476
00:29:32.877 --> 00:29:34.211
Sorry.

477
00:29:34.295 --> 00:29:35.295
Yes.

478
00:29:35.377 --> 00:29:38.335
Well. perhaps.
if it's not too much trouble.

479
00:29:38.419 --> 00:29:40.128
we don't get entertainment.

480
00:29:43.169 --> 00:29:44.169
Why not?

481
00:29:45.669 --> 00:29:49.544
Here's an average. ordinary silver dollar.

482
00:29:56.295 --> 00:29:57.627
Ta-da!

483
00:30:00.253 --> 00:30:01.419
Very good.

484
00:30:01.502 --> 00:30:02.544
Very good.

485
00:30:03.836 --> 00:30:06.502
I will show you a magic trick one day.

486
00:30:08.377 --> 00:30:09.502
What's that?

487
00:30:11.544 --> 00:30:14.044
I am going to escape the hangman's noose.

488
00:30:16.752 --> 00:30:18.878
And how do you plan on doing that?

489
00:30:21.003 --> 00:30:24.544
If I were to tell you.
it would not be a trick.

490
00:30:26.878 --> 00:30:27.878
Nuremberg.

491
00:30:34.211 --> 00:30:35.878
"Do you see
what the Allies are capable of?

492
00:30:35.961 --> 00:30:37.419
"There's nothing left."

493
00:30:43.044 --> 00:30:44.044
"Except that."

494
00:30:53.627 --> 00:30:55.003
Palace of Justice.

495
00:30:56.794 --> 00:30:59.295
The roof's been damaged by the air raids.

496
00:31:00.544 --> 00:31:04.419
Fire gutted the upper floors
and collapsed the clock tower. but...

497
00:31:05.586 --> 00:31:09.419
this courtroom should be able to hold
600 people when it's finished.

498
00:31:10.419 --> 00:31:12.711
What's with all the supplies?

499
00:31:12.794 --> 00:31:15.586
Nazis fought their last stand here
when the city was taken.

500
00:31:15.669 --> 00:31:17.170
And so they will again.

501
00:31:19.711 --> 00:31:22.170
Of all the beautiful cities
in this conquered land.

502
00:31:22.253 --> 00:31:25.170
you want to try them
in this bombed-out husk?

503
00:31:26.794 --> 00:31:30.335
This is Sir David Maxwell-Fyfe.
assistant prosecutor for the British.

504
00:31:31.711 --> 00:31:32.878
Yes. sir. we do.

505
00:31:32.961 --> 00:31:34.502
For one thing. we can control the space.

506
00:31:34.586 --> 00:31:37.461
For another. there's an adjoining prison
with room for up to 1.200 inmates.

507
00:31:38.044 --> 00:31:39.544
We only need space for 22.

508
00:31:40.335 --> 00:31:43.377
I'm sorry. Twenty-two. sir?

509
00:31:43.461 --> 00:31:46.961
That's the number of men
we're indicting for the first trial.

510
00:31:47.044 --> 00:31:51.919
You see. if we don't win that trial.
there won't be any more trials to come.

511
00:31:52.003 --> 00:31:54.544
And you. myself. and Justice Jackson.

512
00:31:54.627 --> 00:31:58.003
and our respective governments
will be the laughingstock of the world.

513
00:31:58.086 --> 00:32:01.170
defeated by the very men we've imprisoned.

514
00:32:01.253 --> 00:32:02.961
So. that will be fun.

515
00:32:04.919 --> 00:32:08.128
My friends in Washington
say opinion's turned against you.

516
00:32:08.211 --> 00:32:09.211
Oh. dear.

517
00:32:09.295 --> 00:32:13.086
There's talk that you won't get
the Chief Justice's seat

518
00:32:13.170 --> 00:32:14.419
when Stone steps down.

519
00:32:14.502 --> 00:32:17.878
Who's Truman gonna pick?
Vinson? Vinson's too political.

520
00:32:17.961 --> 00:32:19.544
Yes. but he's there.

521
00:32:19.627 --> 00:32:21.335
This whole thing's
become a sideshow. Robert.

522
00:32:21.419 --> 00:32:22.502
It hasn't even begun.

523
00:32:23.669 --> 00:32:24.878
They say...

524
00:32:26.295 --> 00:32:28.586
you're writing all the briefs yourself.

525
00:32:28.669 --> 00:32:30.170
refusing help from other lawyers.

526
00:32:30.253 --> 00:32:31.669
Because it has to be done right.

527
00:32:31.753 --> 00:32:33.794
And it will. But you can't do it alone.

528
00:32:33.878 --> 00:32:37.128
Oh. everything will be fine
once we actually get to trial.

529
00:32:37.211 --> 00:32:40.295
You say that as though
trying the Nazi High Command

530
00:32:40.377 --> 00:32:42.878
with untested case law
with the whole world watching

531
00:32:42.961 --> 00:32:43.961
is going to be the easy part.

532
00:32:45.961 --> 00:32:47.753
Well. when you put it like that...

533
00:32:47.836 --> 00:32:52.045
Anything less than total victory
will be considered utter defeat.

534
00:32:52.128 --> 00:32:54.419
Which means.
you don't just have to win. Robert.

535
00:32:54.502 --> 00:32:56.086
you have to be flawless.

536
00:32:57.586 --> 00:32:58.586
No pressure.

537
00:33:01.335 --> 00:33:02.711
I'll have another.

538
00:33:02.794 --> 00:33:04.295
Your cells are made of stone.

539
00:33:05.544 --> 00:33:07.045
9 feet by 13.

540
00:33:08.335 --> 00:33:10.295
Your beds are bolted to the wall.

541
00:33:11.086 --> 00:33:14.377
Your mattresses stuffed with straw
instead of springs.

542
00:33:15.461 --> 00:33:19.586
Your desks are made of cardboard
and will not support a man's full weight.

543
00:33:19.669 --> 00:33:22.669
Your chairs are never allowed
against any wall.

544
00:33:22.753 --> 00:33:26.377
and will be removed
every night at sundown.

545
00:33:27.211 --> 00:33:28.794
When you sleep.

546
00:33:28.878 --> 00:33:32.502
your head and hands will remain
above your blanket. visible at all times.

547
00:33:33.586 --> 00:33:37.045
You will be given no belts.
you'll be given no shoelaces.

548
00:33:37.128 --> 00:33:41.086
you'll be given no toilet seats.
you will be given nothing

549
00:33:41.170 --> 00:33:44.794
with which to use as a weapon
to take your own lives.

550
00:33:47.836 --> 00:33:49.086
Welcome to Nuremberg.

551
00:34:20.336 --> 00:34:21.335
Now this...

552
00:34:22.501 --> 00:34:23.628
is a cell.

553
00:34:24.170 --> 00:34:25.169
You approve?

554
00:34:25.253 --> 00:34:26.419
German-built.

555
00:34:27.793 --> 00:34:29.002
How could I not?

556
00:34:33.878 --> 00:34:35.628
They will charge us soon. yeah?

557
00:34:35.711 --> 00:34:37.461
You're looking forward to it?

558
00:34:37.544 --> 00:34:39.336
I believe I am.

559
00:34:40.669 --> 00:34:46.295
I will have. as you say.
"my day in court."

560
00:34:48.502 --> 00:34:50.377
Do you know this Jackson?

561
00:34:50.461 --> 00:34:52.753
The Justice Jackson?

562
00:34:52.836 --> 00:34:53.920
No. I do not.

563
00:34:54.794 --> 00:34:56.586
He will try to outwit me...

564
00:34:58.295 --> 00:34:59.794
but he will not succeed.

565
00:35:00.502 --> 00:35:02.336
You're very sure of yourself.

566
00:35:02.419 --> 00:35:03.419
Doctor.

567
00:35:04.086 --> 00:35:07.377
no man has ever beaten me.

568
00:35:08.878 --> 00:35:13.003
There are books filled with the names
of those who have tried.

569
00:35:14.544 --> 00:35:15.836
Yet here you sit.

570
00:35:18.669 --> 00:35:19.669
German-built.

571
00:35:22.586 --> 00:35:26.045
You think I am at some sort
of disadvantage

572
00:35:26.128 --> 00:35:27.544
because I sit in a cell?

573
00:35:29.377 --> 00:35:30.628
I will remind you.

574
00:35:31.753 --> 00:35:33.086
I surrendered.

575
00:35:34.212 --> 00:35:37.920
This is exactly where I desire to be.

576
00:35:40.669 --> 00:35:43.170
<i>Göring remains an enigma to me.</i>

577
00:35:43.253 --> 00:35:47.419
<i>The closer we get to the indictments.
the more confident he becomes.</i>

578
00:35:47.502 --> 00:35:49.920
<i>I need to figure out a way
to get closer to him.</i>

579
00:35:50.586 --> 00:35:51.711
So. how do we do that?

580
00:35:55.295 --> 00:35:56.836
We ask for his help.

581
00:35:57.878 --> 00:35:59.586
With what?

582
00:36:01.170 --> 00:36:02.212
Rudolf Hess.

583
00:36:02.878 --> 00:36:04.086
Rudolf...

584
00:36:04.170 --> 00:36:07.170
Rudolf Hess is coming here?

585
00:36:11.253 --> 00:36:14.461
<i>Rudolf Hess.
Deputy to the</i> Führer.

586
00:36:14.544 --> 00:36:17.295
<i>Third in line for succession.
following Hitler and Göring.</i>

587
00:36:19.003 --> 00:36:22.586
<i>Hess transcribed</i> Mein Kampf <i>for Hitler
while the two were in prison.</i>

588
00:36:22.669 --> 00:36:26.086
<i>and was known as one of his most
fanatical followers.</i>

589
00:36:26.170 --> 00:36:27.461
<i>Sieg Heil!</i>

590
00:36:29.711 --> 00:36:31.586
Never do that
in my prison again.

591
00:36:38.878 --> 00:36:41.920
<i>On May 10. 1941.
at the height of the war.</i>

592
00:36:42.003 --> 00:36:45.920
<i>Hess climbed into
a Messerschmitt fighter plane alone</i>

593
00:36:46.003 --> 00:36:47.753
<i>and flew it over the North Sea.</i>

594
00:36:53.295 --> 00:36:56.711
<i>He bailed out somewhere over Scotland
and broke his ankle upon impact.</i>

595
00:36:57.503 --> 00:37:00.836
<i>Upon his discovery.
he announced that he was Rudolf Hess.</i>

596
00:37:00.920 --> 00:37:02.961
<i>third in line of the German High Command.</i>

597
00:37:03.045 --> 00:37:05.003
<i>and he was here on a mission of peace.</i>

598
00:37:05.086 --> 00:37:07.669
<i>and wanted to speak
with Douglas Douglas-Hamilton.</i>

599
00:37:07.753 --> 00:37:09.711
<i>the 13th Duke of Hamilton</i>

600
00:37:09.795 --> 00:37:13.836
<i>whom Hess had met
at the 1936 Olympic Games in Berlin.</i>

601
00:37:14.669 --> 00:37:17.628
<i>After some obstacles.
Hess was granted his meeting.</i>

602
00:37:18.628 --> 00:37:22.419
<i>There. he announced his intention
to meet with King George VI.</i>

603
00:37:22.503 --> 00:37:24.295
<i>have Winston Churchill fired.</i>

604
00:37:24.377 --> 00:37:27.128
<i>and negotiate a truce with Britain.</i>

605
00:37:27.212 --> 00:37:29.753
<i>allowing the two nations to join forces</i>

606
00:37:29.836 --> 00:37:31.878
<i>and defeat the Soviet Union.</i>

607
00:37:33.170 --> 00:37:35.836
<i>Hess was immediately thrown
into the Tower of London.</i>

608
00:37:35.920 --> 00:37:37.795
<i>There. Hess began claiming</i>

609
00:37:37.878 --> 00:37:40.920
<i>he had no memory of past events.
even his childhood.</i>

610
00:37:41.586 --> 00:37:44.920
<i>This lasted until February. 1945.</i>

611
00:37:45.003 --> 00:37:48.461
<i>when he said his previous amnesia
had been faked.</i>

612
00:37:48.544 --> 00:37:49.628
<i>He then flipped again</i>

613
00:37:49.711 --> 00:37:53.544
<i>and said his amnesia
had returned in July. 1945.</i>

614
00:37:53.628 --> 00:37:55.170
<i>when Germany collapsed.</i>

615
00:37:55.253 --> 00:37:57.753
<i>So. now you have come
to Hermann Göring...</i>

616
00:37:58.669 --> 00:38:01.003
to discredit my old friend.

617
00:38:03.378 --> 00:38:06.961
What would be in this for me?

618
00:38:10.461 --> 00:38:11.461
What do you want?

619
00:38:15.212 --> 00:38:16.212
My wife...

620
00:38:17.170 --> 00:38:18.170
and my daughter.

621
00:38:20.045 --> 00:38:22.753
No one has been able to locate them
since I surrendered.

622
00:38:24.253 --> 00:38:26.087
I need you to find them for me. Doctor.

623
00:38:26.753 --> 00:38:29.336
To give to them these.

624
00:38:30.836 --> 00:38:31.836
Letters.

625
00:38:37.461 --> 00:38:38.961
First. we talk to Hess...

626
00:38:40.878 --> 00:38:42.128
and then your family.

627
00:38:44.503 --> 00:38:45.503
How about that?

628
00:38:45.586 --> 00:38:48.045
So. what. this guy almost
takes over the whole world

629
00:38:48.128 --> 00:38:50.711
and now you want us to do
a mail run for him? Doc!

630
00:38:50.795 --> 00:38:53.295
I'm in deeper with this guy
than anyone's ever been.

631
00:38:53.378 --> 00:38:56.295
and meeting his family
will only tell me more.

632
00:38:58.003 --> 00:38:59.586
<i>So. Rudolf...</i>

633
00:39:01.586 --> 00:39:03.212
do you remember me?

634
00:39:07.253 --> 00:39:08.628
We were together. yes.

635
00:39:10.087 --> 00:39:11.544
That must have been the case.

636
00:39:12.836 --> 00:39:14.544
But I don't remember anyone.

637
00:39:17.378 --> 00:39:19.170
It was the three of us. Rudolf.

638
00:39:20.795 --> 00:39:21.795
You...

639
00:39:22.503 --> 00:39:23.503
and I...

640
00:39:25.962 --> 00:39:27.003
and Adolf.

641
00:39:28.795 --> 00:39:30.170
We ruled an empire.

642
00:39:33.544 --> 00:39:34.795
I'm sorry.

643
00:39:39.670 --> 00:39:41.336
You may well have been a friend...

644
00:39:43.795 --> 00:39:45.503
but I don't know you anymore.

645
00:39:51.544 --> 00:39:52.711
<i>He's lying.</i>

646
00:39:54.253 --> 00:39:57.670
He has just spent an hour to say
he does not remember me.

647
00:39:59.628 --> 00:40:02.503
But when he arrived in the prison
and he saw me...

648
00:40:04.003 --> 00:40:05.087
what did he do?

649
00:40:06.295 --> 00:40:07.295
Salute.

650
00:40:08.711 --> 00:40:09.711
<i>Sieg Heil.</i>

651
00:40:13.087 --> 00:40:14.419
That was very good.

652
00:40:20.419 --> 00:40:21.503
This is dumb.

653
00:40:22.128 --> 00:40:23.128
I'm dumb.

654
00:40:23.212 --> 00:40:25.087
- I knew you'd come through for me.
- Yeah.

655
00:40:25.170 --> 00:40:26.920
'Cause I'm a dummy.

656
00:40:32.212 --> 00:40:33.254
How'd you find 'em?

657
00:40:33.336 --> 00:40:35.461
Local gossip told me
they're in Veldenstein.

658
00:40:36.295 --> 00:40:37.295
Smoke?

659
00:40:42.254 --> 00:40:43.419
Never see you smoke.

660
00:40:44.461 --> 00:40:46.003
Yeah. I don't. Gave it up.

661
00:40:47.295 --> 00:40:48.503
My parents hated it.

662
00:40:50.628 --> 00:40:52.045
You always got 'em on ya.

663
00:40:52.128 --> 00:40:54.128
It's a trick to get in good
with the officers.

664
00:40:55.753 --> 00:40:57.836
Tell myself I'll have a smoke
when the war is done.

665
00:40:58.419 --> 00:41:00.045
The war is done. Howie.

666
00:41:01.545 --> 00:41:02.878
It's not too much farther.

667
00:41:23.461 --> 00:41:24.503
Franz?

668
00:41:27.795 --> 00:41:29.254
Mrs. Göring?

669
00:41:30.795 --> 00:41:32.461
Mrs. Göring...

670
00:41:33.670 --> 00:41:35.503
my name is Douglas Kelley.

671
00:41:36.378 --> 00:41:38.545
I work at the prison. I'm a psychiatrist.

672
00:41:49.045 --> 00:41:52.087
Your husband asked me
to bring you some letters.

673
00:41:56.295 --> 00:41:57.295
Hermann?

674
00:41:58.711 --> 00:41:59.711
Yes.

675
00:42:14.545 --> 00:42:15.962
- "How is he?"
- He's good.

676
00:42:17.045 --> 00:42:18.045
He's holdin' up.

677
00:42:31.753 --> 00:42:32.753
Edda.

678
00:42:35.336 --> 00:42:36.419
Was that you playing?

679
00:42:39.628 --> 00:42:40.628
It was beautiful.

680
00:42:53.003 --> 00:42:55.254
Uh. she said.
"He's a friend of your father."

681
00:42:57.420 --> 00:42:58.420
Edda...

682
00:43:02.586 --> 00:43:03.628
"How is Papa?"

683
00:43:05.003 --> 00:43:06.420
Ah. he...

684
00:43:07.878 --> 00:43:09.336
He's doing very well.

685
00:43:10.670 --> 00:43:12.920
- "Is he being brave?"
- Very brave.

686
00:43:15.878 --> 00:43:17.586
He wants you to be brave. too.

687
00:43:25.254 --> 00:43:26.545
He wrote you a letter.

688
00:43:35.254 --> 00:43:36.254
<i>Danke.</i>

689
00:43:40.003 --> 00:43:42.129
"She will read it 100 times. Thank you."

690
00:43:42.212 --> 00:43:43.212
<i>Danke.</i>

691
00:43:51.170 --> 00:43:52.170
<i>Doktor!</i>

692
00:43:58.087 --> 00:43:59.087
For Hermann.

693
00:44:00.670 --> 00:44:01.837
I don't know if I can.

694
00:44:01.920 --> 00:44:02.920
<i>Bitte.</i>

695
00:44:13.878 --> 00:44:14.962
Okay.

696
00:44:16.545 --> 00:44:17.753
Come back.

697
00:44:27.586 --> 00:44:28.586
You okay. Doc?

698
00:44:44.004 --> 00:44:45.004
What the hell?

699
00:44:53.254 --> 00:44:54.461
What's goin' on?

700
00:44:54.545 --> 00:44:57.296
Word came down a couple of hours ago.
We're charging the prisoners.

701
00:44:58.212 --> 00:44:59.212
Where have you been?

702
00:45:14.378 --> 00:45:15.378
Hermann Göring?

703
00:45:16.586 --> 00:45:19.586
I am <i>Reichsmarschall</i> Hermann Göring.

704
00:45:20.254 --> 00:45:22.545
Hermann Wilhelm Göring.
you are hereby charged

705
00:45:22.628 --> 00:45:24.920
by the United States of America.
the French Republic.

706
00:45:25.004 --> 00:45:27.045
United Kingdom of Great Britain
and Northern Ireland

707
00:45:27.129 --> 00:45:30.545
and the Union of Soviet Socialist
Republics on the following four counts.

708
00:45:30.628 --> 00:45:33.795
Crimes against Peace. War Crimes.
Crimes against Humanity

709
00:45:33.878 --> 00:45:36.712
and of a Common Plan or Conspiracy
to commit those Crimes.

710
00:45:36.795 --> 00:45:39.378
The Crimes against Humanity
you're accused of include murder.

711
00:45:39.461 --> 00:45:42.628
extermination. enslavement.
deportation. and other inhumane acts.

712
00:45:42.712 --> 00:45:44.753
This is a copy of your indictment.
Do you have any questions?

713
00:45:46.837 --> 00:45:47.837
<i>Nein.</i>

714
00:45:49.045 --> 00:45:50.045
Good day.

715
00:45:52.004 --> 00:45:53.170
Who's next?

716
00:45:53.254 --> 00:45:54.254
Streicher.

717
00:46:05.170 --> 00:46:06.878
Do you have any questions?

718
00:46:11.336 --> 00:46:12.545
What did he say?

719
00:46:14.004 --> 00:46:16.087
He said he wants a Jewish lawyer.

720
00:46:18.254 --> 00:46:19.545
"I'm not going to trial."

721
00:46:20.545 --> 00:46:21.795
You are. Dr. Ley.

722
00:46:25.254 --> 00:46:26.545
"I never killed anyone."

723
00:46:29.045 --> 00:46:30.378
Guards!

724
00:46:30.461 --> 00:46:31.712
It's okay. it's okay.

725
00:46:31.795 --> 00:46:32.795
- Don't touch me.
- It's okay.

726
00:46:32.879 --> 00:46:33.962
- Robert. Robert...
- Don't touch me!

727
00:46:34.045 --> 00:46:35.420
- Whoa. whoa!
- Hold him!

728
00:46:35.503 --> 00:46:36.420
Come on!

729
00:46:36.503 --> 00:46:37.503
Get a hold of him!

730
00:46:37.587 --> 00:46:40.753
Don't try me as a common criminal!
Come on!

731
00:46:40.837 --> 00:46:43.045
Shoot me! Shoot me!

732
00:46:43.129 --> 00:46:44.670
Shoot me!

733
00:47:12.879 --> 00:47:13.879
Rough day?

734
00:47:14.795 --> 00:47:16.378
Lady from the train.

735
00:47:16.962 --> 00:47:18.045
Magic man.

736
00:47:19.212 --> 00:47:20.545
How goes the secret mission?

737
00:47:22.753 --> 00:47:24.420
It's hit a few obstacles.

738
00:47:27.461 --> 00:47:28.587
I can see that.

739
00:47:29.795 --> 00:47:31.212
What are you doing here?

740
00:47:32.712 --> 00:47:34.129
I came in with the press.

741
00:47:34.879 --> 00:47:37.129
Hermann Göring and the Nazis
are being indicted today.

742
00:47:37.212 --> 00:47:38.336
You don't say?

743
00:47:39.461 --> 00:47:41.545
Strap yourself in.

744
00:47:42.670 --> 00:47:45.296
This city is about to become
"The Greatest Show on Earth."

745
00:48:15.004 --> 00:48:16.004
From your wife.

746
00:48:20.045 --> 00:48:21.045
You saw her?

747
00:48:24.962 --> 00:48:26.045
<i>Danke schön.</i> Doctor.

748
00:48:37.587 --> 00:48:41.378
<i>Dateline Nuremberg!
As dark rumors continue to swirl</i>

749
00:48:41.462 --> 00:48:43.962
<i>about the true purpose
of the Nazi work camps.</i>

750
00:48:44.045 --> 00:48:47.129
<i>the legal teams are assembling
for what promises to be</i>

751
00:48:47.212 --> 00:48:48.962
<i>the trial of the century.</i>

752
00:48:49.045 --> 00:48:52.503
<i>Through this tunnel.
the Nazis will be taken to the courtroom.</i>

753
00:48:52.587 --> 00:48:54.795
<i>now being rebuilt for the trial.</i>

754
00:48:54.879 --> 00:48:56.503
<i>There. the film lights will be so bright</i>

755
00:48:56.587 --> 00:48:59.837
<i>that the court-goers
will be provided with sunglasses.</i>

756
00:48:59.920 --> 00:49:02.004
<i>Hermann Göring
and his Hitler-loving cronies</i>

757
00:49:02.087 --> 00:49:04.587
<i>are scheduled to face off
with our boys in one week.</i>

758
00:49:04.670 --> 00:49:08.503
<i>Will justice prevail?
Or will the fascists go free?</i>

759
00:49:08.587 --> 00:49:12.920
<i>This reporter desperately hopes
that the Allies run into no problems.</i>

760
00:49:14.212 --> 00:49:15.212
We have a problem.

761
00:49:15.296 --> 00:49:19.171
Operation Weserübung
was the German invasion of Denmark

762
00:49:19.254 --> 00:49:20.754
and Norway in 1940.

763
00:49:20.837 --> 00:49:22.378
Textbook aggressive war.

764
00:49:22.462 --> 00:49:24.962
The Nazis. they roll tanks in.
they occupy neutral country.

765
00:49:25.046 --> 00:49:29.545
Except they're going to claim
that the invasion was a preemptive strike.

766
00:49:29.628 --> 00:49:30.879
To preempt what?

767
00:49:31.628 --> 00:49:32.962
The British plan to invade Norway.

768
00:49:33.046 --> 00:49:35.212
- Well. that's ridiculous.
- Absolutely ridiculous.

769
00:49:35.879 --> 00:49:37.336
I'm in complete agreement.

770
00:49:38.628 --> 00:49:41.254
It concerns me that you're in this room
right now.

771
00:49:41.336 --> 00:49:44.545
Well. in addition to being ridiculous.

772
00:49:44.628 --> 00:49:45.795
it also happens to be true.

773
00:49:45.879 --> 00:49:49.462
The idea was to use the country
as a staging area to hold the Nazis back.

774
00:49:49.545 --> 00:49:53.254
We can't prosecute the Nazis
for planning aggressive wars

775
00:49:53.337 --> 00:49:55.628
if you guys were planning aggressive wars.

776
00:49:55.712 --> 00:49:57.129
I admit there's a certain logic there.

777
00:49:57.212 --> 00:49:58.587
Can the Nazis prove it?

778
00:49:58.670 --> 00:50:00.712
The German lawyer's
already put in a request for documents.

779
00:50:00.795 --> 00:50:02.795
-but they don't have it. Not yet.
-Then we're in the clear.

780
00:50:02.879 --> 00:50:03.879
Maybe.

781
00:50:05.129 --> 00:50:07.254
But it raises a bigger issue.

782
00:50:08.212 --> 00:50:12.337
We have to know what the Nazis know.
what their defense strategy is.

783
00:50:13.004 --> 00:50:15.046
How exactly do you propose we do that?

784
00:50:18.503 --> 00:50:22.962
<i>Dr. Kelley. you are going to meet
someone very important this evening.</i>

785
00:50:24.087 --> 00:50:26.670
<i>This might actually be your chance
to finally be of some use.</i>

786
00:50:32.503 --> 00:50:33.670
Impressive. right?

787
00:50:36.962 --> 00:50:40.004
Hitler was building it
to be the largest stadium on the planet.

788
00:50:42.337 --> 00:50:43.670
You're Justice Jackson.

789
00:50:44.837 --> 00:50:45.962
And you're the shrink.

790
00:50:47.795 --> 00:50:49.712
This is where they held the rallies.

791
00:50:49.795 --> 00:50:53.879
Every year. Hitler would pack this place.
speak to the Nazi Party as a whole.

792
00:50:55.046 --> 00:50:56.129
They filmed it.

793
00:50:58.503 --> 00:51:02.171
In 1935. this is where he announced
the Nuremberg Laws.

794
00:51:02.754 --> 00:51:03.837
You know the laws?

795
00:51:05.962 --> 00:51:07.962
The Nuremberg Laws defined a Jew

796
00:51:08.046 --> 00:51:11.254
as any person having
three or four Jewish grandparents.

797
00:51:12.629 --> 00:51:14.837
And it didn't matter
if you practiced Judaism.

798
00:51:14.921 --> 00:51:19.503
if you'd converted to Christianity.
this was about blood.

799
00:51:22.087 --> 00:51:25.462
The laws stripped all Jews
of German citizenry.

800
00:51:26.754 --> 00:51:30.587
They made it illegal for Jews and Germans
to marry each other

801
00:51:30.670 --> 00:51:32.879
because of the fear of <i>Rassenschande.</i>

802
00:51:33.712 --> 00:51:35.462
Defilement of the blood.

803
00:51:38.129 --> 00:51:42.587
Under the laws. Jews were prohibited
from using state hospitals.

804
00:51:43.337 --> 00:51:47.171
and not allowed access to public education
beyond the age of 14.

805
00:51:48.754 --> 00:51:52.004
Libraries. parks. and beaches
were closed to Jews.

806
00:51:53.462 --> 00:51:56.629
War memorials
had all Jewish names on them...

807
00:51:57.962 --> 00:51:58.962
expunged.

808
00:52:00.296 --> 00:52:05.004
All of that was announced right here.
on this very ground.

809
00:52:09.462 --> 00:52:10.712
What do you want from me?

810
00:52:12.503 --> 00:52:14.087
Your patients...

811
00:52:15.296 --> 00:52:18.213
I need you to start asking them
the right questions.

812
00:52:21.462 --> 00:52:23.213
What are the right questions?

813
00:52:24.420 --> 00:52:26.213
What they tell their lawyers.

814
00:52:26.296 --> 00:52:28.420
How they plan to defend themselves.

815
00:52:33.004 --> 00:52:34.420
You want me to be a spy.

816
00:52:36.254 --> 00:52:38.046
I want you to do your duty
for your country.

817
00:52:38.129 --> 00:52:41.504
No. you want me to break
doctor-patient confidentiality.

818
00:52:41.587 --> 00:52:44.879
I think you already have. Doctor.
We read every report.

819
00:52:45.754 --> 00:52:46.754
We need more.

820
00:52:58.504 --> 00:52:59.795
Why not just shoot them?

821
00:53:01.795 --> 00:53:03.213
That's what everybody wants.

822
00:53:04.004 --> 00:53:06.213
-I mean. if you're just gonna cheat...
-It's not cheating.

823
00:53:06.296 --> 00:53:08.420
If you're asking me to betray my oath...

824
00:53:11.213 --> 00:53:13.378
why not just shoot them
and be done with it?

825
00:53:16.962 --> 00:53:19.796
After the last Great War.
we made Germany crawl.

826
00:53:21.545 --> 00:53:23.087
We humiliated them.

827
00:53:23.171 --> 00:53:25.420
Made them pay reparations
they couldn't afford.

828
00:53:26.962 --> 00:53:30.629
We made them hate us so much that
in less than two decades.

829
00:53:31.712 --> 00:53:35.171
they went from a broken nation
to near world conquerors.

830
00:53:36.921 --> 00:53:39.046
We have to do this right.
because if we don't...

831
00:53:40.587 --> 00:53:43.754
if 15 years from now.
they come back even stronger...

832
00:53:45.587 --> 00:53:47.670
I don't know if we can beat 'em
a third time.

833
00:53:50.921 --> 00:53:53.420
If we just shoot these men.
we make 'em martyrs.

834
00:53:54.504 --> 00:53:55.962
I'm not gonna allow them that.

835
00:53:57.254 --> 00:53:59.046
There will be no statues of them.

836
00:54:00.420 --> 00:54:01.962
No songs of praise.

837
00:54:04.296 --> 00:54:06.587
I'm gonna put Hermann Göring
on the stand

838
00:54:07.962 --> 00:54:10.296
and I'm gonna make him tell the world
what he did.

839
00:54:12.337 --> 00:54:14.213
So that it can never happen again.

840
00:54:18.254 --> 00:54:19.420
Hmm.

841
00:54:22.254 --> 00:54:23.837
You brought me here because of Göring?

842
00:54:24.962 --> 00:54:25.962
No.

843
00:54:29.337 --> 00:54:33.962
I brought you here to show you
that before the bullets were fired.

844
00:54:35.462 --> 00:54:37.962
before tens of millions of men died...

845
00:54:40.754 --> 00:54:42.670
all of this started with laws.

846
00:54:44.379 --> 00:54:47.629
This war ends in a courtroom.

847
00:54:49.962 --> 00:54:50.962
With Göring.

848
00:54:51.962 --> 00:54:53.754
He's the face of the Nazis now.

849
00:54:55.046 --> 00:54:56.962
As he falls. so do they all.

850
00:54:59.254 --> 00:55:00.837
But if I'm gonna do that. I...

851
00:55:03.171 --> 00:55:04.629
I need to be ready for him.

852
00:55:09.171 --> 00:55:10.296
Will you help me?

853
00:55:27.921 --> 00:55:29.004
Let's talk about Hitler.

854
00:55:33.420 --> 00:55:37.004
It is interesting you have not
asked me this directly before.

855
00:55:37.921 --> 00:55:40.671
I'm curious what the attraction was.

856
00:55:42.296 --> 00:55:44.171
He was a failed painter. right?

857
00:55:44.254 --> 00:55:48.420
Not a very good soldier.
yet he's worshiped and revered.

858
00:55:51.129 --> 00:55:52.921
He made us feel German again.

859
00:55:58.462 --> 00:55:59.462
How?

860
00:56:01.504 --> 00:56:03.671
Well. the war had seen Germany crushed.

861
00:56:04.796 --> 00:56:10.671
And along comes a man who says.
"We can reclaim our former glory."

862
00:56:13.296 --> 00:56:14.963
Would you not follow a man like this?

863
00:56:16.379 --> 00:56:18.337
Depends what else he wanted to do.

864
00:56:21.712 --> 00:56:25.337
The first time I saw Hitler talk.
it was. uh...

865
00:56:27.254 --> 00:56:28.296
1922.

866
00:56:29.254 --> 00:56:32.545
Upstairs of a coffee shop.
For maybe 30 people.

867
00:56:34.254 --> 00:56:35.337
This was peacetime.

868
00:56:35.420 --> 00:56:39.129
but it was a peace without food.
jobs. shoes.

869
00:56:40.587 --> 00:56:42.587
And he stood up. and he said.

870
00:56:42.671 --> 00:56:46.921
"French bellies are being filled
with German pain."

871
00:56:48.255 --> 00:56:49.255
Then.

872
00:56:50.462 --> 00:56:53.545
"If you make threats.
you need bayonets.

873
00:56:54.171 --> 00:56:56.754
"Rearm! Down with Versailles!"

874
00:56:59.046 --> 00:57:02.921
So. that night.
I became a National Socialist.

875
00:57:04.921 --> 00:57:08.004
Off of... one speech?

876
00:57:08.088 --> 00:57:11.462
Well. I could tell he would appeal
to the old soldiers.

877
00:57:11.545 --> 00:57:14.088
If we have the old soldiers.
we have the manpower.

878
00:57:14.171 --> 00:57:18.213
Even with his anti-Semitism.
it served a practical purpose.

879
00:57:18.921 --> 00:57:23.004
It brought towards us men who needed
something else to focus their emotions.

880
00:57:23.088 --> 00:57:24.379
Something else to blame.

881
00:57:27.379 --> 00:57:28.379
And the camps?

882
00:57:33.712 --> 00:57:39.004
They were to be work camps
for our political opponents. nothing more.

883
00:57:39.921 --> 00:57:41.129
And you signed off on that?

884
00:57:41.754 --> 00:57:42.921
For work camps. yeah.

885
00:57:43.004 --> 00:57:44.837
Do you not think

886
00:57:44.921 --> 00:57:48.420
that the Japanese interned by
the Americans after Pearl Harbor

887
00:57:48.504 --> 00:57:50.420
were not put to work?
Of course. they were.

888
00:57:52.796 --> 00:57:55.921
I made the camps for the good of Germany.
for the war effort.

889
00:57:58.171 --> 00:57:59.296
Not for death.

890
00:58:01.671 --> 00:58:03.671
Himmler. Heydrich.

891
00:58:04.754 --> 00:58:05.963
They were responsible?

892
00:58:08.420 --> 00:58:12.462
If it is true what they say happened
in the camps...

893
00:58:14.546 --> 00:58:17.587
this is a grave blight
on the great German Reich.

894
00:58:21.296 --> 00:58:23.213
Have you told your lawyer about this?

895
00:58:25.796 --> 00:58:29.420
Douglas. I will not stand
against the <i>Führer.</i>

896
00:58:31.420 --> 00:58:33.420
Not even if it could help you?

897
00:58:33.504 --> 00:58:36.504
These are not things people
need to know. Doctor.

898
00:58:38.879 --> 00:58:39.879
Only you.

899
00:58:42.504 --> 00:58:44.046
He can be sympathetic.

900
00:58:45.629 --> 00:58:47.255
It's gonna be a problem for you.

901
00:58:47.337 --> 00:58:50.088
He seriously claims that he thought
they were only work camps?

902
00:58:50.171 --> 00:58:51.587
-That's right.
-You believe him?

903
00:58:53.671 --> 00:58:56.088
Himmler ran the camps. right?

904
00:58:56.171 --> 00:58:57.337
He was the head of the SS.

905
00:58:57.420 --> 00:58:59.255
Göring was the head of the Air Force.

906
00:58:59.337 --> 00:59:01.796
How often in America
does the head of the Air Force know

907
00:59:01.879 --> 00:59:03.671
what the head
of the Secret Service is doing?

908
00:59:03.754 --> 00:59:06.671
I'm sorry. but I cannot believe that
we're having this conversation right now.

909
00:59:06.754 --> 00:59:08.462
-I'm doing what you asked.
-No!

910
00:59:08.546 --> 00:59:10.587
- You're apologizing for him.
- Gentlemen. please.

911
00:59:10.671 --> 00:59:13.046
-I'm not the one defending the Nazi.
-You think I'm defending him?

912
00:59:13.130 --> 00:59:15.379
I am analyzing him. you provincial moron.

913
00:59:17.046 --> 00:59:20.213
Göring is. above all things. a narcissist.

914
00:59:21.004 --> 00:59:25.046
The only thing he cares about is building
Germany up and then becoming her leader.

915
00:59:25.130 --> 00:59:26.879
He does not care about the Jews.

916
00:59:26.963 --> 00:59:29.296
- So. he's fine with them dying.
- And he's fine with them not.

917
00:59:29.379 --> 00:59:33.088
The only thing Hermann Göring cares about
is Hermann Göring.

918
00:59:33.171 --> 00:59:36.088
Does that sound like a man
who dedicates himself

919
00:59:36.171 --> 00:59:38.379
to the extermination of an entire race?

920
00:59:42.046 --> 00:59:44.879
Well. Dr. Kelley. I really appreciate
your thoughtfulness on this.

921
00:59:44.963 --> 00:59:46.879
but I have to admit. it is very hard...

922
00:59:48.046 --> 00:59:49.046
to believe.

923
00:59:50.879 --> 00:59:54.130
You wanna walk into that courtroom
with a handful of assumptions.

924
00:59:55.046 --> 00:59:56.046
fine.

925
00:59:57.421 --> 00:59:59.130
But he will eat you for breakfast.

926
01:00:12.296 --> 01:00:14.629
"I would like to apologize
for my outburst earlier.

927
01:00:14.713 --> 01:00:16.004
"I'm feeling much better."

928
01:00:17.713 --> 01:00:18.879
That's good. Dr. Ley.

929
01:00:24.296 --> 01:00:26.671
"And. you?
Something seems to be troubling you."

930
01:00:29.754 --> 01:00:30.796
I'm fine.

931
01:00:37.046 --> 01:00:38.046
"Don't worry."

932
01:00:42.088 --> 01:00:43.671
"This will all
be over soon."

933
01:00:50.171 --> 01:00:52.296
<i>Ley's mood is markedly improved.</i>

934
01:00:53.213 --> 01:00:56.754
<i>He told us he has begun
making arrangements for his defense.</i>

935
01:00:57.796 --> 01:01:01.838
<i>I feel as though. for the first time.
he's reached out to me.</i>

936
01:01:04.462 --> 01:01:05.796
Oh. shit.

937
01:01:06.462 --> 01:01:07.546
Hurry! Move!

938
01:01:07.629 --> 01:01:08.796
Doc! Come quick!

939
01:01:14.046 --> 01:01:15.796
Jesus!

940
01:01:22.713 --> 01:01:25.088
Ripped out the hem of his towel
to make a rope.

941
01:01:26.796 --> 01:01:29.796
Stuffed his underwear into his mouth
so he wouldn't scream and then...

942
01:01:31.963 --> 01:01:33.754
just leaned forward.

943
01:01:33.838 --> 01:01:36.046
Apparently. with a great deal
of determination.

944
01:01:37.587 --> 01:01:38.838
You didn't see any of this coming?

945
01:01:39.337 --> 01:01:40.713
He told me he was doing better.

946
01:01:42.838 --> 01:01:43.921
"Told you"?

947
01:01:46.213 --> 01:01:47.629
You're supposed to keep them alive.

948
01:01:58.421 --> 01:02:00.255
I'm bringing in another doctor.

949
01:02:00.337 --> 01:02:03.713
It's been determined a second opinion
is required for some of your patients.

950
01:02:05.379 --> 01:02:07.462
Dr. Gilbert arrives this afternoon.

951
01:02:08.130 --> 01:02:09.297
You will brief him.

952
01:02:15.504 --> 01:02:17.588
How do you feel about suicide?

953
01:02:23.213 --> 01:02:25.588
The last refuge of cowards. yeah.

954
01:02:27.588 --> 01:02:30.088
Or the last act of a desperate man?

955
01:02:32.005 --> 01:02:34.130
There are always exceptions. of course.

956
01:02:38.171 --> 01:02:40.879
You are in trouble.

957
01:02:41.462 --> 01:02:42.588
Why would you say that?

958
01:02:42.671 --> 01:02:45.671
New doctor. New tests.

959
01:02:45.754 --> 01:02:48.838
Since Ley died. they no longer trust you.

960
01:02:49.754 --> 01:02:50.838
You're wrong.

961
01:02:52.005 --> 01:02:54.255
Douglas...

962
01:02:55.921 --> 01:02:58.504
when you are in a position of power...

963
01:03:00.838 --> 01:03:02.671
they will always come after you.

964
01:03:03.546 --> 01:03:05.504
You have to protect yourself.

965
01:03:05.588 --> 01:03:08.671
Why would I have to protect myself
from my allies?

966
01:03:09.297 --> 01:03:14.713
Just because a man is your ally
does not mean he is on your side.

967
01:03:15.838 --> 01:03:18.088
My father was a diplomat.
Did I tell you this?

968
01:03:18.171 --> 01:03:19.171
-No.
-Ah.

969
01:03:22.880 --> 01:03:23.880
Yeah.

970
01:03:24.880 --> 01:03:28.754
He was... ...posted to Africa.

971
01:03:30.462 --> 01:03:33.671
And it was there he was
to meet his best friend.

972
01:03:34.504 --> 01:03:38.921
A man named Hermann von Epstein.

973
01:03:40.754 --> 01:03:42.546
I was named after him.

974
01:03:45.754 --> 01:03:48.754
Yeah. I was named for a Jew.

975
01:03:50.421 --> 01:03:54.713
We loved Uncle Hermann so much.

976
01:03:54.796 --> 01:03:57.671
He was very rich.

977
01:03:58.255 --> 01:04:01.297
He lived in Veldenstein Castle.

978
01:04:01.880 --> 01:04:04.005
And when I was six years old.

979
01:04:05.796 --> 01:04:09.046
he moved my entire family in with him.

980
01:04:10.379 --> 01:04:11.379
Can you imagine?

981
01:04:12.421 --> 01:04:15.297
It was a child's dream
to live in such a castle.

982
01:04:16.462 --> 01:04:20.046
I would run down the halls.
pretending I was a knight.

983
01:04:21.172 --> 01:04:23.713
I would stare down from the battlements.

984
01:04:23.796 --> 01:04:27.088
envisioning armies swarming to attack.

985
01:04:28.629 --> 01:04:33.754
Uncle Hermann. he lived in the largest
and most beautiful room on the top floor.

986
01:04:34.629 --> 01:04:38.172
Down the hall. my mother had a bedroom.
also beautiful.

987
01:04:40.213 --> 01:04:41.421
My father...

988
01:04:43.963 --> 01:04:46.463
he lived in a small bedroom
on the ground floor.

989
01:04:48.713 --> 01:04:54.005
And I was to realize
just how rich Uncle Hermann was.

990
01:04:55.213 --> 01:04:58.337
So rich that he could move my family in.

991
01:04:59.588 --> 01:05:02.713
So rich that he could put my father
on the ground floor.

992
01:05:05.255 --> 01:05:07.337
So rich that. whenever he wanted.

993
01:05:08.921 --> 01:05:10.796
he could walk down the hall...

994
01:05:13.921 --> 01:05:15.546
and enjoy my mother.

995
01:05:18.755 --> 01:05:20.546
Just because a man is your ally

996
01:05:21.921 --> 01:05:24.713
does not mean he is on your side.

997
01:05:33.088 --> 01:05:36.629
You found Hermann Göring
to be "imaginative"?

998
01:05:36.713 --> 01:05:39.088
I didn't find him to be that way.
the test did.

999
01:05:39.838 --> 01:05:42.255
Well. that is what
a second opinion is for.

1000
01:05:42.838 --> 01:05:47.921
Which...
...brings us to Rudolf Hess.

1001
01:05:48.713 --> 01:05:53.088
I'm inclined to believe
that his amnesia is genuine.

1002
01:05:53.172 --> 01:05:55.546
You mean the part where he forgets
about being a Nazi?

1003
01:05:56.337 --> 01:05:58.130
Okay. Look. Dr. Kelley.

1004
01:05:59.047 --> 01:06:02.838
I'm not here to step on your toes. okay?

1005
01:06:02.921 --> 01:06:05.130
I'll share research. We'll co-author.

1006
01:06:06.337 --> 01:06:07.629
Co-author what?

1007
01:06:07.713 --> 01:06:10.963
You don't have to play coy with me.
We're both here for the same reason.

1008
01:06:12.421 --> 01:06:14.755
Now. two books
about the Nazi High Command.

1009
01:06:14.838 --> 01:06:16.463
that's gonna cut into the market.

1010
01:06:16.546 --> 01:06:18.546
I say we write it together.

1011
01:06:19.213 --> 01:06:21.755
-Hmm?
-Mm-hmm.

1012
01:06:25.172 --> 01:06:26.629
Good luck with your tests.

1013
01:06:41.130 --> 01:06:42.130
<i>Doktor.</i>

1014
01:06:46.880 --> 01:06:48.088
<i>Danke schön.</i>

1015
01:07:55.172 --> 01:07:56.421
She was surprised?

1016
01:07:56.504 --> 01:07:59.880
Oh. she was. uh. astounded.

1017
01:07:59.963 --> 01:08:01.088
Teach me this trick.

1018
01:08:01.963 --> 01:08:03.421
-The coin behind the ear?
-Yeah. yeah.

1019
01:08:03.504 --> 01:08:07.005
Teach me this trick.
so I too can astound her.

1020
01:08:08.087 --> 01:08:09.088
Hmm.

1021
01:08:09.755 --> 01:08:12.713
- I gave my silver dollar to your daughter.
- Ah.

1022
01:08:13.504 --> 01:08:14.838
It's the simplest trick in the world.

1023
01:08:14.922 --> 01:08:17.504
It works because. you know.
people want to believe.

1024
01:08:18.171 --> 01:08:21.212
Well. you hold up the dollar.
and you say.

1025
01:08:21.297 --> 01:08:25.255
"Hey. folks! Here is an ordinary.
average silver dollar."

1026
01:08:27.171 --> 01:08:29.712
Then you put it in your other hand.
All right?

1027
01:08:31.171 --> 01:08:32.255
You focus on it.

1028
01:08:34.671 --> 01:08:36.963
But really. it's right here.

1029
01:08:38.755 --> 01:08:40.795
You palm it in your right hand.

1030
01:08:40.880 --> 01:08:42.503
-Palm it.
-Yeah.

1031
01:08:42.588 --> 01:08:45.420
You keep it between these two fingers...

1032
01:08:45.504 --> 01:08:47.213
...and you wrap your palm
around it.

1033
01:08:47.297 --> 01:08:49.171
but you focus on your left hand.

1034
01:08:51.796 --> 01:08:54.879
And you feel the coin in there.
the weight of it. Right?

1035
01:08:54.963 --> 01:08:58.922
And if you believe it.
then they'll believe it.

1036
01:09:00.963 --> 01:09:05.546
And then. you just.
well. you reach behind the ear...

1037
01:09:06.130 --> 01:09:10.213
- Abracadabra!
- Hmm.

1038
01:09:12.588 --> 01:09:13.880
What is "abracadabra"?

1039
01:09:14.379 --> 01:09:15.963
Uh. it's the magic words.

1040
01:09:16.046 --> 01:09:18.712
It. uh. gives the illusion. uh...

1041
01:09:18.796 --> 01:09:21.005
...a cosmic weight.

1042
01:09:21.588 --> 01:09:24.005
And it always must be "abracadabra"?

1043
01:09:24.087 --> 01:09:26.004
No. no. It could be anything.

1044
01:09:26.088 --> 01:09:28.087
It could be "presto."

1045
01:09:29.963 --> 01:09:31.838
I think I prefer "abracadabra."

1046
01:09:31.922 --> 01:09:34.296
So. it was your father
who taught you this trick?

1047
01:09:34.379 --> 01:09:37.214
Uh... my father? No.

1048
01:09:38.880 --> 01:09:41.214
You say that like it is unthinkable.

1049
01:09:42.047 --> 01:09:43.379
Yeah. my father was content

1050
01:09:43.463 --> 01:09:48.214
to ply his trade
and display a cheerful disposition.

1051
01:09:50.588 --> 01:09:52.505
He was a man of no accomplishment.

1052
01:09:53.088 --> 01:09:54.338
But you believe...

1053
01:09:56.338 --> 01:09:57.922
you are destined for more.

1054
01:09:59.880 --> 01:10:02.047
You want to be known as a great man.

1055
01:10:08.088 --> 01:10:09.088
Yes.

1056
01:10:09.172 --> 01:10:11.255
And I am your ticket.

1057
01:10:14.671 --> 01:10:17.963
You will return to America
as the great scholar of the Nazis.

1058
01:10:19.379 --> 01:10:23.630
and I will have a trick
to impress my daughter

1059
01:10:24.546 --> 01:10:26.047
when this trial is done.

1060
01:10:32.838 --> 01:10:34.463
You stopped taking me with you to see him.

1061
01:10:38.671 --> 01:10:40.214
Didn't want to bother you so late.

1062
01:10:41.755 --> 01:10:43.588
You've been seeing him a lot without me.

1063
01:10:44.713 --> 01:10:45.922
What're you doing. Doc?

1064
01:10:47.838 --> 01:10:49.172
Trying to learn something.

1065
01:10:50.505 --> 01:10:52.214
You sure that's what this is still about?

1066
01:10:55.880 --> 01:10:56.922
Good night. Howie.

1067
01:11:07.463 --> 01:11:09.505
How are you gonna
defend yourself. Hermann?

1068
01:11:09.588 --> 01:11:11.130
Oh.

1069
01:11:11.671 --> 01:11:13.963
- Would not you like to know?
- I'm serious.

1070
01:11:18.463 --> 01:11:19.671
Are we friends. Doctor?

1071
01:11:21.922 --> 01:11:25.963
I think that word is a little too simple
for what we are.

1072
01:11:28.671 --> 01:11:30.214
But are you asking me this...

1073
01:11:31.880 --> 01:11:32.963
as a friend?

1074
01:11:36.214 --> 01:11:37.214
I am.

1075
01:11:42.047 --> 01:11:46.214
Tomorrow
when I enter my plea.

1076
01:11:48.214 --> 01:11:49.755
I will read a statement.

1077
01:11:50.671 --> 01:11:51.922
I am going to say

1078
01:11:53.130 --> 01:11:56.963
that I assume all responsibility
for my actions.

1079
01:11:57.047 --> 01:11:58.421
I will refuse. however.

1080
01:11:59.214 --> 01:12:02.963
to accept responsibility
for acts committed by others

1081
01:12:03.047 --> 01:12:04.380
that I was unaware of.

1082
01:12:05.963 --> 01:12:07.922
and I would not have approved of.

1083
01:12:11.338 --> 01:12:12.421
What I did...

1084
01:12:15.672 --> 01:12:17.047
I did for my country.

1085
01:12:18.838 --> 01:12:20.922
Tell me you would not do the same
for yours.

1086
01:12:39.297 --> 01:12:42.130
They told me I could find you here.

1087
01:12:46.005 --> 01:12:47.630
In seven hours...

1088
01:12:50.005 --> 01:12:52.964
the whole world is going to be focused
on this room.

1089
01:12:55.005 --> 01:12:56.130
This is it.

1090
01:12:57.338 --> 01:12:58.380
This is everything.

1091
01:13:05.130 --> 01:13:08.505
This is the statement
that Göring plans on reading tomorrow.

1092
01:13:15.713 --> 01:13:16.797
Thank you.

1093
01:14:10.421 --> 01:14:11.797
Atten-hut!

1094
01:14:18.797 --> 01:14:19.797
Let's go.

1095
01:14:35.797 --> 01:14:36.797
Here they come!

1096
01:14:41.463 --> 01:14:42.421
Jesus!

1097
01:15:48.172 --> 01:15:49.214
All rise!

1098
01:16:33.880 --> 01:16:35.214
May it please Your Honors...

1099
01:16:38.755 --> 01:16:42.922
The privilege of opening the first trial
in history

1100
01:16:43.755 --> 01:16:46.256
for crimes against the peace
of the world

1101
01:16:46.338 --> 01:16:48.839
imposes a grave responsibility.

1102
01:16:50.922 --> 01:16:54.131
The wrongs which we seek
to condemn and punish

1103
01:16:55.172 --> 01:16:56.714
have been so calculated...

1104
01:16:57.755 --> 01:17:00.297
<i>...so malignant.
and so devastating</i>

1105
01:17:01.256 --> 01:17:05.047
that civilization cannot tolerate
their being ignored.

1106
01:17:06.380 --> 01:17:09.256
because we cannot survive
their being repeated.

1107
01:17:12.463 --> 01:17:16.714
In the prisoners' dock
sit 20-odd broken men.

1108
01:17:17.964 --> 01:17:22.672
We will show them to be living symbols
of racial hatred.

1109
01:17:24.256 --> 01:17:26.922
of terrorism and violence.

1110
01:17:28.505 --> 01:17:33.297
and of the arrogance and cruelty of power.

1111
01:17:35.338 --> 01:17:37.839
<i>Civilization
can afford no compromise</i>

1112
01:17:38.839 --> 01:17:42.089
<i>by dealing ambiguously or indecisively.</i>

1113
01:17:42.172 --> 01:17:47.672
with the men in whom these forces
now precariously survive.

1114
01:17:52.714 --> 01:17:54.880
Wars are no longer local.

1115
01:17:57.214 --> 01:18:02.214
All modern wars become world wars.
eventually.

1116
01:18:04.755 --> 01:18:07.839
And none of the big nations can stay out.

1117
01:18:09.505 --> 01:18:14.755
But the ultimate step
in avoiding periodic wars

1118
01:18:14.839 --> 01:18:17.797
in a system of international lawlessness

1119
01:18:19.298 --> 01:18:23.256
is to make statesmen
responsible for the law!

1120
01:18:25.964 --> 01:18:27.505
And let me make clear

1121
01:18:27.588 --> 01:18:31.338
that while this law is first applied
against German aggressors.

1122
01:18:31.422 --> 01:18:34.338
it must condemn aggression
by any other nation

1123
01:18:34.422 --> 01:18:36.922
including those who sit here now.
in judgement.

1124
01:18:38.422 --> 01:18:43.422
We are able to do away
with domestic tyranny

1125
01:18:43.505 --> 01:18:45.463
and violence and aggression

1126
01:18:45.547 --> 01:18:48.338
by those in power against the rights
of their own people...

1127
01:18:50.006 --> 01:18:52.463
only when we make all men

1128
01:18:53.839 --> 01:18:56.006
answerable to the law.

1129
01:19:10.505 --> 01:19:11.672
Hermann Göring.

1130
01:19:14.298 --> 01:19:18.839
The defendants are to plead guilty
or not guilty to the charges against them.

1131
01:19:19.797 --> 01:19:24.714
They will proceed. in turn. to a point
in the dock opposite to the microphone.

1132
01:19:38.256 --> 01:19:40.047
I am Hermann Wilhelm Göring.

1133
01:19:40.131 --> 01:19:42.338
I stand before the Court today...

1134
01:19:42.422 --> 01:19:44.298
...and the world...

1135
01:19:44.380 --> 01:19:45.672
<i>...and pledge
only to tell...</i>

1136
01:19:48.131 --> 01:19:49.881
The Tribunal
has reached the decision

1137
01:19:50.463 --> 01:19:53.964
that the defendants are not entitled
to make a statement.

1138
01:19:55.047 --> 01:19:58.755
They will be permitted to address
the Court prior to their sentencing.

1139
01:20:01.589 --> 01:20:03.089
As <i>Reichsmarschall</i> of Germany...

1140
01:20:03.172 --> 01:20:05.089
You are not <i>Reichsmarschall</i> here.

1141
01:20:06.131 --> 01:20:08.922
You are only Hermann Göring. the prisoner.

1142
01:20:09.589 --> 01:20:12.505
Do you plead guilty or not guilty?

1143
01:20:49.131 --> 01:20:50.131
Emmy!

1144
01:20:51.463 --> 01:20:52.463
Edda!

1145
01:20:53.881 --> 01:20:54.881
Emmy!

1146
01:20:56.630 --> 01:20:59.256
What happened? What happened?
Where are they?

1147
01:21:00.672 --> 01:21:02.214
What? Where are they?

1148
01:21:02.298 --> 01:21:03.714
-They took them!
-Who?

1149
01:21:04.672 --> 01:21:05.922
Americans!

1150
01:21:20.881 --> 01:21:21.881
Emmy!

1151
01:21:22.881 --> 01:21:24.547
Emmy! Edda!

1152
01:21:26.797 --> 01:21:28.131
Emmy. Edda.

1153
01:21:29.298 --> 01:21:31.089
Emmy! Emmy Göring!

1154
01:21:36.298 --> 01:21:38.547
Yeah?

1155
01:21:41.505 --> 01:21:44.922
I need a favor.

1156
01:21:45.006 --> 01:21:46.131
You gotta be shitting me.

1157
01:21:47.464 --> 01:21:48.797
Thanks. I'm gonna need it.

1158
01:21:50.589 --> 01:21:52.714
They've arrested Emmy Göring

1159
01:21:53.298 --> 01:21:56.214
on suspicion of complicity
with her husband's art thefts.

1160
01:21:56.298 --> 01:21:58.505
Kid goes to the nuns. No contact allowed.

1161
01:21:59.131 --> 01:22:00.338
They're women and children.

1162
01:22:01.505 --> 01:22:02.589
Yeah.

1163
01:22:03.756 --> 01:22:05.173
Sir. we're supposed to be
better than this.

1164
01:22:05.256 --> 01:22:06.714
It's out of my hands!

1165
01:22:08.298 --> 01:22:09.298
And you're welcome.

1166
01:22:13.173 --> 01:22:14.214
By the way.

1167
01:22:14.964 --> 01:22:16.380
how did you know where she was hiding?

1168
01:22:28.505 --> 01:22:30.006
Did Edda play for you again?

1169
01:22:33.214 --> 01:22:35.048
-She did.
-Ah.

1170
01:22:36.048 --> 01:22:37.422
She's very talented.

1171
01:22:38.048 --> 01:22:39.298
She likes you.

1172
01:22:42.048 --> 01:22:43.630
Do you have their letters?

1173
01:22:45.464 --> 01:22:46.464
No.

1174
01:22:47.464 --> 01:22:49.964
No letters. unfortunately.

1175
01:22:50.048 --> 01:22:51.048
No?

1176
01:22:52.298 --> 01:22:53.298
Next time.

1177
01:22:58.839 --> 01:23:00.298
And here's my new doctor.

1178
01:23:01.173 --> 01:23:03.214
We were just talking about my family.

1179
01:23:03.298 --> 01:23:05.964
Ah. yes. Well. I was sorry
to hear about that.

1180
01:23:08.298 --> 01:23:09.505
About what?

1181
01:23:09.589 --> 01:23:10.881
Their arrest.

1182
01:23:10.964 --> 01:23:13.881
Your wife and daughter were arrested
five days ago.

1183
01:23:15.589 --> 01:23:16.714
He didn't tell you?

1184
01:23:22.464 --> 01:23:23.464
Hey.

1185
01:23:23.547 --> 01:23:25.214
Hey! What the hell was that?

1186
01:23:25.881 --> 01:23:29.964
That was me being honest with my patient.
something you oughta try sometime.

1187
01:23:30.048 --> 01:23:31.547
You destroyed him in there.

1188
01:23:31.630 --> 01:23:32.630
So?

1189
01:23:34.839 --> 01:23:37.422
What the hell is wrong with you?
What's wrong with you. hmm?

1190
01:23:39.339 --> 01:23:41.214
- Hey. stop!
- Hey. stop!

1191
01:23:42.630 --> 01:23:45.797
Jesus Christ.
You're mental health professionals!

1192
01:23:46.339 --> 01:23:47.589
For Christ's sake!

1193
01:23:51.464 --> 01:23:55.048
Dr. Gilbert. would you like me to place
Dr. Kelley under arrest?

1194
01:23:59.631 --> 01:24:02.089
-No. sir.
-Then get out of my goddamn office!

1195
01:24:06.922 --> 01:24:09.214
Cinema.

1196
01:24:13.173 --> 01:24:14.214
All rise!

1197
01:24:28.672 --> 01:24:30.006
May it please the Court.

1198
01:24:30.089 --> 01:24:34.298
the prosecution would now like to enter
into evidence the following film footage.

1199
01:24:34.756 --> 01:24:39.214
The images you are about to see have
never before been shown in public.

1200
01:24:39.923 --> 01:24:42.547
This film should offer a brief explanation

1201
01:24:43.505 --> 01:24:46.756
of what the words
"concentration camp" implied.

1202
01:25:02.672 --> 01:25:06.631
<i>These are the locations of
the largest concentration and prison camps</i>

1203
01:25:06.714 --> 01:25:10.631
<i>maintained throughout Germany
and occupied Europe under the Nazi regime.</i>

1204
01:25:13.589 --> 01:25:15.756
<i>The 4th Armored Division
of General Patton's Third Army</i>

1205
01:25:15.839 --> 01:25:17.714
<i>liberated this camp early in April.</i>

1206
01:25:20.756 --> 01:25:24.131
<i>They see the woodshed where
lime-covered bodies are stacked in layers</i>

1207
01:25:24.215 --> 01:25:25.964
<i>and the stench is overpowering.</i>

1208
01:25:35.756 --> 01:25:37.797
<i>Slave labor camp at Nordhausen</i>

1209
01:25:37.881 --> 01:25:40.589
<i>liberated by the 3rd Armored Division.
First Army.</i>

1210
01:25:40.672 --> 01:25:43.298
<i>At least 3.000 political prisoners
died here</i>

1211
01:25:43.380 --> 01:25:46.380
<i>at the brutal hands of SS troops
and pardoned German criminals</i>

1212
01:25:46.464 --> 01:25:47.964
<i>who were the camp guard.</i>

1213
01:25:48.048 --> 01:25:49.881
<i>Nordhausen had been a depository</i>

1214
01:25:49.964 --> 01:25:53.797
<i>for slaves found unfit for work
in the underground V-bomb plants</i>

1215
01:25:53.881 --> 01:25:56.048
<i>and in other German camps and factories.</i>

1216
01:26:01.006 --> 01:26:04.173
<i>Amid the corpses are human skeletons
too weak to move.</i>

1217
01:26:08.881 --> 01:26:11.589
<i>Men of our medical battalions
worked two days and nights</i>

1218
01:26:11.672 --> 01:26:13.839
<i>binding wounds and giving medications.</i>

1219
01:26:13.923 --> 01:26:16.714
<i>But for advanced cases
of starvation and tuberculosis.</i>

1220
01:26:16.797 --> 01:26:18.756
<i>there were often no cures.</i>

1221
01:26:19.506 --> 01:26:23.256
<i>The survivors are shown being evacuated
for treatment in Allied hospitals.</i>

1222
01:26:36.089 --> 01:26:39.298
<i>I'm Lieutenant Senior Grade
Jack H. Taylor. US Navy.</i>

1223
01:26:39.380 --> 01:26:40.714
<i>from Hollywood. California.</i>

1224
01:26:40.798 --> 01:26:43.756
<i>Believe it or not. this is the first time
I've ever been in the movies.</i>

1225
01:26:43.839 --> 01:26:46.089
<i>I was captured December 1st.</i>

1226
01:26:46.964 --> 01:26:50.173
<i>I was taken to this
Mauthausen Concentration Lager.</i>

1227
01:26:50.798 --> 01:26:52.714
<i>an extermination camp.</i>

1228
01:26:53.589 --> 01:27:00.298
<i>where we have been starving
and... and beaten and killed.</i>

1229
01:27:00.923 --> 01:27:03.672
<i>Uh. fortunately. my turn hadn't come.</i>

1230
01:27:04.631 --> 01:27:08.547
<i>Uh... there were...</i>

1231
01:27:08.631 --> 01:27:09.964
<i>How many ways
do they execute?</i>

1232
01:27:10.798 --> 01:27:11.798
<i>Five or six ways.</i>

1233
01:27:11.881 --> 01:27:15.006
<i>By gas. by shooting. by beating.</i>

1234
01:27:15.089 --> 01:27:16.589
<i>That is. beating with clubs.</i>

1235
01:27:17.339 --> 01:27:18.506
<i>Uh...</i>

1236
01:27:19.631 --> 01:27:21.964
<i>By exposure.</i>

1237
01:27:22.714 --> 01:27:25.422
<i>That is. standing out in the snow
naked for 48 hours</i>

1238
01:27:25.506 --> 01:27:29.173
<i>and having cold water thrown on them
in the middle of winter.</i>

1239
01:27:29.256 --> 01:27:30.380
<i>Starvation.</i>

1240
01:27:31.798 --> 01:27:32.881
<i>Dogs.</i>

1241
01:27:32.964 --> 01:27:35.547
<i>And pushing over a 100-foot cliff.</i>

1242
01:27:37.339 --> 01:27:40.798
<i>This is all true. has been seen.
and is now being recorded.</i>

1243
01:27:45.923 --> 01:27:48.339
<i>Nationalities and prison numbers
are tattooed</i>

1244
01:27:48.422 --> 01:27:50.173
<i>on the stomachs of the inmates.</i>

1245
01:27:58.839 --> 01:27:59.839
<i>In the official report.</i>

1246
01:27:59.923 --> 01:28:03.339
<i>the Buchenwald camp is termed
an extermination factory.</i>

1247
01:28:04.631 --> 01:28:08.422
<i>Bodies stacked one upon the other
were found outside the crematory.</i>

1248
01:28:11.589 --> 01:28:13.422
<i>A body disposal plant.</i>

1249
01:28:13.506 --> 01:28:16.006
<i>Inside are the ovens
which gave the crematorium</i>

1250
01:28:16.090 --> 01:28:20.506
<i>a maximum disposal capacity
of about 400 bodies per 10-hour day.</i>

1251
01:28:24.339 --> 01:28:26.131
<i>Dachau. near München.</i>

1252
01:28:26.215 --> 01:28:28.339
<i>one of the oldest
of the Nazi prison camps.</i>

1253
01:28:44.464 --> 01:28:47.839
<i>This is what the liberators found
inside the buildings.</i>

1254
01:29:13.964 --> 01:29:16.547
<i>Hanging in orderly rows
were the clothes of prisoners</i>

1255
01:29:16.631 --> 01:29:19.006
<i>who had been suffocated
in a lethal gas chamber.</i>

1256
01:29:20.173 --> 01:29:22.673
<i>They had been persuaded
to remove their clothing</i>

1257
01:29:22.756 --> 01:29:27.422
<i>under the pretext of taking a shower.
for which towels and soap were provided.</i>

1258
01:29:33.131 --> 01:29:35.422
<i>Sanitary conditions were so appalling</i>

1259
01:29:35.506 --> 01:29:39.256
<i>that heavy equipment had to be brought in
to speed the work of cleaning up.</i>

1260
01:30:00.673 --> 01:30:02.881
<i>This was Bergen-Belsen.</i>

1261
01:30:30.881 --> 01:30:32.173
How's that possible?

1262
01:30:42.756 --> 01:30:44.006
What I just saw.

1263
01:30:49.839 --> 01:30:51.090
How is it possible?

1264
01:30:54.673 --> 01:30:55.798
Himmler.

1265
01:30:56.506 --> 01:30:58.215
Himmler wasn't second-in-command.

1266
01:30:59.215 --> 01:31:00.215
You were.

1267
01:31:00.839 --> 01:31:02.215
1.200 camps?

1268
01:31:03.048 --> 01:31:05.422
No. What am I supposed to believe.
that you didn't know?

1269
01:31:05.506 --> 01:31:07.131
Anyone can fake an atrocity.

1270
01:31:07.215 --> 01:31:09.798
So. you're saying the film was a fake.
That's your defense?

1271
01:31:09.881 --> 01:31:10.923
What would you have me say?

1272
01:31:11.006 --> 01:31:12.839
How about the truth for once?

1273
01:31:12.923 --> 01:31:13.923
Why?

1274
01:31:14.756 --> 01:31:16.381
So you can run and tell Jackson?

1275
01:31:18.090 --> 01:31:19.464
My friend.

1276
01:31:21.048 --> 01:31:22.548
your hypocrisy is stunning.

1277
01:31:23.548 --> 01:31:24.548
My hypocrisy?

1278
01:31:24.631 --> 01:31:26.965
You think American bullets and bombs
don't kill people?

1279
01:31:27.589 --> 01:31:32.090
You vaporize 150.000 Japanese
at the touch of a button.

1280
01:31:32.173 --> 01:31:35.840
and you presume to stand in judgement
on me for war crimes?

1281
01:31:35.923 --> 01:31:37.422
We had every right to defend ourselves.

1282
01:31:37.506 --> 01:31:40.090
How do you defend yourself
on someone else's soil?

1283
01:31:40.173 --> 01:31:42.631
There's a difference
between us bombing war factories

1284
01:31:42.714 --> 01:31:45.257
and civilians dying as collateral damage.

1285
01:31:45.339 --> 01:31:48.798
and you building
1.200 human slaughterhouses

1286
01:31:48.881 --> 01:31:52.048
designed to exterminate an entire race.

1287
01:31:52.131 --> 01:31:54.131
and you know it!

1288
01:31:54.215 --> 01:31:55.965
What do you think war is?

1289
01:31:59.673 --> 01:32:00.714
Not what I saw today.

1290
01:32:00.798 --> 01:32:04.215
What do you think the Russians do
to German prisoners of war?

1291
01:32:04.298 --> 01:32:07.006
You have your freedom.
and I am a prisoner

1292
01:32:07.090 --> 01:32:09.506
because you won. and we lost.

1293
01:32:09.589 --> 01:32:11.965
Not because you are morally superior!

1294
01:32:12.840 --> 01:32:16.132
This trial will be a farce in 15 years.

1295
01:32:16.215 --> 01:32:19.132
Great conquerors are not thought of
as murderers.

1296
01:32:19.798 --> 01:32:21.881
Genghis Khan. Alexander the Great...

1297
01:32:21.965 --> 01:32:24.006
You are not Alexander the Great!

1298
01:32:25.965 --> 01:32:28.464
You are a fat man in a cell.

1299
01:32:30.631 --> 01:32:32.048
And you knew.

1300
01:32:32.881 --> 01:32:34.090
Hmm.

1301
01:32:36.673 --> 01:32:38.840
I have made a mistake.

1302
01:32:43.215 --> 01:32:44.923
You are not destined for more.

1303
01:32:46.464 --> 01:32:50.215
You will have an unhappy life. I think.

1304
01:32:52.756 --> 01:32:55.173
It will all be overshadowed by this.

1305
01:32:56.464 --> 01:32:58.048
by the time spent with me.

1306
01:32:59.423 --> 01:33:02.215
You will write your volumes.
try to re-live it.

1307
01:33:03.215 --> 01:33:05.090
The one moment in your life

1308
01:33:06.589 --> 01:33:08.673
when you actually stood with greatness.

1309
01:33:09.257 --> 01:33:10.881
You think you're a great man?

1310
01:33:14.132 --> 01:33:15.589
You think that's your legacy?

1311
01:33:16.215 --> 01:33:17.714
At least I will have one.

1312
01:33:18.548 --> 01:33:21.339
You will leave no mark on this world.

1313
01:33:22.423 --> 01:33:24.048
I am the book!

1314
01:33:24.132 --> 01:33:26.840
You are merely a footnote.

1315
01:33:31.923 --> 01:33:33.548
They are gonna kill you.

1316
01:33:35.506 --> 01:33:37.048
They are gonna hang you

1317
01:33:37.881 --> 01:33:40.715
by the neck till you piss yourself...

1318
01:33:41.881 --> 01:33:42.881
and die.

1319
01:33:45.756 --> 01:33:47.006
Your wife will be a widow.

1320
01:33:48.715 --> 01:33:50.715
Your daughter will be an orphan.

1321
01:33:54.132 --> 01:33:56.173
And you will have done that to yourself.

1322
01:34:28.840 --> 01:34:30.215
I know who you are.

1323
01:34:31.840 --> 01:34:33.173
What's he like?

1324
01:34:33.840 --> 01:34:34.881
You don't wanna know.

1325
01:34:35.840 --> 01:34:38.048
Jackson's putting him on the stand
day after tomorrow.

1326
01:34:38.132 --> 01:34:39.132
Hmm.

1327
01:34:40.423 --> 01:34:43.007
Jackson's gonna get killed.

1328
01:34:43.589 --> 01:34:45.007
Why do you say that?

1329
01:34:46.339 --> 01:34:49.173
Because Göring is ready for him.

1330
01:34:52.132 --> 01:34:53.756
He was ready for all of us.

1331
01:34:58.007 --> 01:35:02.215
Why don't you tell me all about it?

1332
01:35:04.007 --> 01:35:06.090
Look at that.

1333
01:35:06.173 --> 01:35:10.048
Your private conversations
with Hermann Göring made the front page.

1334
01:35:10.132 --> 01:35:11.548
- Sir. I...
- You're finished.

1335
01:35:12.715 --> 01:35:14.923
I signed your transfer order this morning.

1336
01:35:15.007 --> 01:35:17.589
You're to be sent back to the States
where you'll be discharged.

1337
01:35:18.339 --> 01:35:21.506
You have embarrassed me and this office
for the last time.

1338
01:35:24.132 --> 01:35:25.423
I'm sorry. Colonel.

1339
01:35:27.257 --> 01:35:28.257
You deserved better.

1340
01:35:28.339 --> 01:35:29.423
Yes. I did.

1341
01:35:31.798 --> 01:35:36.173
And just so you know. we are releasing
Göring's wife and daughter.

1342
01:35:36.965 --> 01:35:38.715
You were right. We are better than that.

1343
01:35:43.923 --> 01:35:46.215
-Thank you. sir.
-Your train's at five o'clock.

1344
01:35:47.673 --> 01:35:50.299
Don't take this the wrong way.
but I never wanna see you again.

1345
01:36:05.381 --> 01:36:06.965
Came to say goodbye?

1346
01:36:07.756 --> 01:36:10.715
Did you really mean it
when you said Jackson had no chance?

1347
01:36:10.798 --> 01:36:11.798
Sure.

1348
01:36:11.881 --> 01:36:14.007
It's all just a big show
for the cameras anyway.

1349
01:36:14.756 --> 01:36:16.215
So. it doesn't matter
what happens tomorrow.

1350
01:36:16.299 --> 01:36:18.673
If Göring beats Jackson. so be it.

1351
01:36:18.756 --> 01:36:20.048
Yeah. I don't believe that.

1352
01:36:22.756 --> 01:36:23.756
Neither do you.

1353
01:36:25.631 --> 01:36:27.882
You know more about him
than anybody on earth.

1354
01:36:29.173 --> 01:36:30.506
Yeah. that's right. I do.

1355
01:36:31.923 --> 01:36:35.673
I spent thousands of hours with him.
I run hundreds of tests.

1356
01:36:35.756 --> 01:36:37.464
You know what sets him apart from us?

1357
01:36:39.048 --> 01:36:40.132
Nothing.

1358
01:36:41.756 --> 01:36:42.756
I know.

1359
01:36:44.840 --> 01:36:45.840
You know?

1360
01:36:47.007 --> 01:36:48.423
'Cause I'm one of 'em.

1361
01:36:50.381 --> 01:36:51.464
What are you talking about?

1362
01:36:52.965 --> 01:36:54.464
I'm German. Doc.

1363
01:36:56.423 --> 01:36:57.673
I grew up in Munich.

1364
01:36:58.756 --> 01:37:01.423
You grew up in Detroit.
You said your mom spoke German.

1365
01:37:01.506 --> 01:37:03.715
She did. So did my father.

1366
01:37:05.756 --> 01:37:07.007
'Cause I was raised here.

1367
01:37:07.590 --> 01:37:09.007
You're an American soldier.

1368
01:37:12.048 --> 01:37:13.048
Why'd you leave?

1369
01:37:16.174 --> 01:37:17.257
Why do you think?

1370
01:37:23.174 --> 01:37:24.174
You're a Jew.

1371
01:37:32.923 --> 01:37:35.007
You know. with the blonde hair
and the blue eyes.

1372
01:37:35.090 --> 01:37:36.715
I never got hassled much.

1373
01:37:39.840 --> 01:37:43.590
My father was a patriot who fought
for Germany in the First World War.

1374
01:37:46.423 --> 01:37:47.882
We loved this country.

1375
01:37:49.965 --> 01:37:51.715
Eventually. he realized we had to get out.

1376
01:37:55.381 --> 01:37:56.381
How'd you do it?

1377
01:37:58.257 --> 01:38:00.174
The problem was getting travel visas.

1378
01:38:02.007 --> 01:38:03.631
Other countries wouldn't take us.

1379
01:38:04.965 --> 01:38:07.965
My dad had a cousin in New York
who helped.

1380
01:38:09.631 --> 01:38:11.798
We finally got our exit visas in 1940.

1381
01:38:14.007 --> 01:38:16.215
But we only had enough money
for one ticket out.

1382
01:38:19.631 --> 01:38:21.132
My little sister Margot...

1383
01:38:23.423 --> 01:38:25.007
she was only 11. so.

1384
01:38:25.923 --> 01:38:27.798
my parents didn't want her
traveling alone.

1385
01:38:29.715 --> 01:38:30.715
So they sent me.

1386
01:38:34.423 --> 01:38:36.423
Boy. I was seasick the whole way.

1387
01:38:40.631 --> 01:38:42.882
When I landed. I stayed with my cousin.

1388
01:38:45.673 --> 01:38:47.215
And the Nazis invaded Holland.

1389
01:38:51.882 --> 01:38:53.132
My family never showed up.

1390
01:38:57.339 --> 01:38:58.673
That's when I went to Detroit.

1391
01:39:01.132 --> 01:39:03.590
Got a job as an apprentice
in a tool factory.

1392
01:39:04.673 --> 01:39:07.132
Learned English listenin' to baseball
on the radio.

1393
01:39:09.215 --> 01:39:10.506
When Pearl Harbor happened...

1394
01:39:12.423 --> 01:39:15.465
I was the first one
at the recruitment office to enlist.

1395
01:39:18.215 --> 01:39:19.215
You know what they said?

1396
01:39:20.923 --> 01:39:24.132
They couldn't take me
'cause I wasn't an American citizen.

1397
01:39:26.631 --> 01:39:28.631
I'd have to wait to get drafted.

1398
01:39:31.673 --> 01:39:32.673
So I did.

1399
01:39:33.965 --> 01:39:35.631
I waited. and I waited.

1400
01:39:35.715 --> 01:39:39.132
and I checked the mailbox every day
for two years.

1401
01:39:42.299 --> 01:39:44.049
June 6. 1944...

1402
01:39:45.757 --> 01:39:48.590
landed at Omaha Beach on D-Day.

1403
01:39:53.840 --> 01:39:55.090
Four years earlier...

1404
01:39:57.798 --> 01:40:02.631
I left this country scared and alone
in the middle of the night.

1405
01:40:06.840 --> 01:40:09.299
But I came back with a goddamn army.

1406
01:40:13.340 --> 01:40:14.423
I found Margot.

1407
01:40:16.548 --> 01:40:18.923
She's in Switzerland.

1408
01:40:19.007 --> 01:40:21.548
She's 16 now. She's living with relatives.

1409
01:40:23.673 --> 01:40:24.673
She's good.

1410
01:40:26.090 --> 01:40:27.090
She made it.

1411
01:40:29.007 --> 01:40:30.007
And your folks?

1412
01:40:32.840 --> 01:40:37.423
Records show that my parents
arrived at Auschwitz.

1413
01:40:37.506 --> 01:40:39.423
August 12. 1942.

1414
01:40:42.673 --> 01:40:46.340
Camp was liberated January 27. 1945.

1415
01:40:50.632 --> 01:40:51.632
No sign of 'em.

1416
01:40:54.423 --> 01:40:57.049
The Nazis had a name
for what they did to us.

1417
01:41:01.090 --> 01:41:02.423
"The Final Solution."

1418
01:41:06.965 --> 01:41:08.423
Like we were...

1419
01:41:10.840 --> 01:41:13.715
just some kinda nagging puzzle

1420
01:41:13.798 --> 01:41:16.299
that they finally figured out
how to solve.

1421
01:41:20.090 --> 01:41:21.506
So sorry. Howie.

1422
01:41:23.548 --> 01:41:25.465
I'm gonna tell Streicher.

1423
01:41:28.798 --> 01:41:29.924
I'm gonna tell him.

1424
01:41:30.673 --> 01:41:33.423
Right before they put
that rope around his neck.

1425
01:41:33.506 --> 01:41:36.590
I'm gonna tell that piece of shit
that he was confiding in a Jew.

1426
01:41:41.506 --> 01:41:45.132
You say it doesn't matter
what happens tomorrow.

1427
01:41:50.673 --> 01:41:51.673
It matters.

1428
01:41:54.423 --> 01:41:55.548
More than you know.

1429
01:41:57.757 --> 01:41:58.757
Matters to me.

1430
01:42:01.216 --> 01:42:02.216
To my family.

1431
01:42:03.381 --> 01:42:04.757
To all of Germany.

1432
01:42:05.257 --> 01:42:06.548
Göring has to fall.

1433
01:42:14.506 --> 01:42:16.673
If you think he's gonna beat Jackson...

1434
01:42:18.882 --> 01:42:22.340
Doc. please just do something about it.

1435
01:42:26.548 --> 01:42:27.548
I can't.

1436
01:42:30.924 --> 01:42:31.924
You can't?

1437
01:42:34.965 --> 01:42:36.049
I'm just a shrink.

1438
01:42:53.548 --> 01:42:55.715
You wanna know
why it happened here?

1439
01:42:58.673 --> 01:43:00.007
'Cause people let it happen.

1440
01:43:01.882 --> 01:43:04.216
'Cause they didn't stand up
until it was too late.

1441
01:43:07.090 --> 01:43:08.715
Have a safe trip home. Doc.

1442
01:43:21.840 --> 01:43:23.465
Yes. sir. Of course.

1443
01:43:25.715 --> 01:43:28.840
No. I... I completely understand.

1444
01:43:31.340 --> 01:43:32.340
Thank you.

1445
01:43:35.548 --> 01:43:36.548
Son of a gun.

1446
01:43:38.799 --> 01:43:42.673
Truman just named Frederick Vinson
Chief Justice of the Supreme Court.

1447
01:43:42.757 --> 01:43:43.757
Oh.

1448
01:43:45.548 --> 01:43:47.340
Ah. I didn't want the job anyway.

1449
01:43:47.423 --> 01:43:48.423
Who would?

1450
01:43:50.548 --> 01:43:51.548
Bottoms up.

1451
01:43:54.965 --> 01:43:56.299
You're walking into a trap.

1452
01:43:56.381 --> 01:43:59.174
Dr. Kelley. I was under the impression
you'd been relieved.

1453
01:43:59.257 --> 01:44:01.882
Putting Göring on the stand
gives him everything he wants.

1454
01:44:01.965 --> 01:44:03.965
It's why he surrendered
in the first place.

1455
01:44:04.049 --> 01:44:06.924
His last chance to redeem the Reich
on the world stage.

1456
01:44:07.007 --> 01:44:08.548
After what I read
in the paper this morning.

1457
01:44:08.632 --> 01:44:10.590
I don't believe
I care what you think anymore.

1458
01:44:10.673 --> 01:44:12.216
-You can't beat him!
-Guards!

1459
01:44:12.299 --> 01:44:13.882
Not without help.

1460
01:44:15.174 --> 01:44:16.882
This is everything I have on him.

1461
01:44:16.965 --> 01:44:19.632
Private files. off-the-book conversations.

1462
01:44:19.715 --> 01:44:22.007
I know more about this man
than anyone else on the planet

1463
01:44:22.091 --> 01:44:23.381
and it's all in here.

1464
01:44:27.465 --> 01:44:28.465
Why do you have this?

1465
01:44:30.632 --> 01:44:31.840
I was gonna write a book.

1466
01:44:34.299 --> 01:44:35.924
Make something of myself. yeah.

1467
01:44:37.882 --> 01:44:38.882
Mmm.

1468
01:44:40.007 --> 01:44:41.007
It's okay.

1469
01:44:42.715 --> 01:44:45.091
So. you really think I can't beat him?

1470
01:44:45.174 --> 01:44:46.216
Honestly?

1471
01:44:48.799 --> 01:44:50.049
I don't know.

1472
01:44:51.216 --> 01:44:53.091
You know. I was gonna be Chief Justice.

1473
01:44:54.965 --> 01:44:58.216
Now I'll be lucky if there's a place
on the Court for me when I return.

1474
01:44:58.299 --> 01:45:01.465
As of six hours ago.
I was discharged from the army.

1475
01:45:02.257 --> 01:45:04.299
There's nothing left for us to do. sir.

1476
01:45:07.091 --> 01:45:09.007
Might as well go finish the war.

1477
01:45:14.924 --> 01:45:15.924
Mmm-hmm.

1478
01:45:19.007 --> 01:45:21.882
<i>The trick is to use
his vanity against him.</i>

1479
01:45:23.548 --> 01:45:25.715
<i>He is the </i>Reichsmarschall.

1480
01:45:25.799 --> 01:45:28.299
<i>And the</i> Reichsmarschall <i>is never wrong.</i>

1481
01:45:28.965 --> 01:45:29.965
<i>He can't be.</i>

1482
01:45:30.674 --> 01:45:35.382
<i>Every decision that's led him
to this place has to be the right one.</i>

1483
01:45:35.465 --> 01:45:38.423
<i>So. as much as he won't wanna
talk about the camps</i>

1484
01:45:38.507 --> 01:45:40.924
<i>and the SS and the Final Solution.</i>

1485
01:45:41.924 --> 01:45:43.465
<i>you can make him own them.</i>

1486
01:45:44.632 --> 01:45:45.882
<i>Kelley's right.</i>

1487
01:45:45.965 --> 01:45:48.757
<i>Get him to admit to signing those orders.</i>

1488
01:45:49.423 --> 01:45:50.632
and you'll have him.

1489
01:45:52.465 --> 01:45:53.465
I'll have him.

1490
01:45:57.132 --> 01:45:58.132
This is your day.

1491
01:45:59.465 --> 01:46:00.465
You're ready.

1492
01:47:11.966 --> 01:47:14.299
Sergeant. what is Doug Kelley
still doing here?

1493
01:47:16.632 --> 01:47:17.632
No idea. sir.

1494
01:47:20.924 --> 01:47:22.007
All rise!

1495
01:47:36.423 --> 01:47:39.132
Justice Jackson. are you ready?

1496
01:47:57.340 --> 01:48:00.507
The prosecution now calls
Hermann Göring to the stand.

1497
01:48:49.674 --> 01:48:53.966
For the record. is there any doubt
in your mind that Adolf Hitler is dead?

1498
01:48:57.966 --> 01:48:59.382
I have no doubt.

1499
01:49:00.882 --> 01:49:04.632
So. you are aware that this makes you
the only living man

1500
01:49:04.715 --> 01:49:08.757
who can expound to us the true purposes
of the Nazi Party

1501
01:49:08.841 --> 01:49:10.757
and the inner workings of its leadership?

1502
01:49:12.133 --> 01:49:14.091
I am perfectly aware of this. yeah.

1503
01:49:14.174 --> 01:49:15.133
Mmm-hmm.

1504
01:49:16.049 --> 01:49:21.007
Your party. from the very beginning.
intended to overthrow the Weimar Republic?

1505
01:49:23.423 --> 01:49:25.174
That was our firm intention.

1506
01:49:26.423 --> 01:49:27.590
What the hell?

1507
01:49:27.674 --> 01:49:29.007
And upon coming to power.

1508
01:49:29.091 --> 01:49:32.216
you immediately abolished
parliamentary government in Germany?

1509
01:49:32.299 --> 01:49:34.590
We found it to be no longer necessary.

1510
01:49:35.590 --> 01:49:38.966
Is that because you believed people
are not capable of self-government?

1511
01:49:41.715 --> 01:49:46.799
We were elected by the people
and given a mandate for change.

1512
01:49:47.382 --> 01:49:49.465
<i>The system
that had previously existed</i>

1513
01:49:49.549 --> 01:49:52.258
<i>had brought Germany to the verge of ruin.</i>

1514
01:49:52.340 --> 01:49:54.715
<i>Your own President Roosevelt said.</i>

1515
01:49:54.799 --> 01:49:59.299
"There are certain peoples in Europe
who have forsaken democracy

1516
01:49:59.382 --> 01:50:01.632
"not because they did not wish for it.

1517
01:50:02.507 --> 01:50:06.258
"but because democracy had brought forth
men who were too weak."

1518
01:50:08.007 --> 01:50:09.632
Get to war crimes.

1519
01:50:10.133 --> 01:50:11.549
After you came to power.

1520
01:50:11.632 --> 01:50:16.424
you regarded it necessary to suppress
all opposition parties. correct?

1521
01:50:16.507 --> 01:50:20.674
We found it necessary
to no longer permit opposition. yeah.

1522
01:50:21.133 --> 01:50:23.549
And you also considered it
immediately necessary

1523
01:50:23.632 --> 01:50:25.465
to establish concentration camps?

1524
01:50:26.507 --> 01:50:30.549
The camps were set up as a measure
against the Communists

1525
01:50:31.216 --> 01:50:32.549
and their violence.

1526
01:50:32.632 --> 01:50:35.590
So. it was necessary
to erect a camp for them.

1527
01:50:35.674 --> 01:50:37.841
One. two. or three camps.
something like this.

1528
01:50:38.674 --> 01:50:41.590
You also had to have certain groups

1529
01:50:41.674 --> 01:50:44.841
to carry out orders
and fight for you if necessary. right?

1530
01:50:45.757 --> 01:50:46.882
Certain groups?

1531
01:50:46.966 --> 01:50:49.258
Well. for example.
if you wanted certain people killed.

1532
01:50:50.133 --> 01:50:52.590
you had to have some organization
that would kill them.

1533
01:50:53.882 --> 01:50:56.174
Yeah. Germany had this level
of political police

1534
01:50:56.258 --> 01:50:57.716
as you would find in any other country.

1535
01:50:57.799 --> 01:50:59.299
And the SA and the SS

1536
01:50:59.382 --> 01:51:02.258
were the organizations
that carried out these orders

1537
01:51:02.340 --> 01:51:05.299
and dealt with people on a physical level.
were they not?

1538
01:51:05.382 --> 01:51:08.632
The SA never received orders
to kill anybody.

1539
01:51:08.716 --> 01:51:10.632
Neither did the SS. Not in my time.

1540
01:51:10.716 --> 01:51:13.299
Beyond a certain point.
I had no influence on it.

1541
01:51:14.258 --> 01:51:16.674
Well. the SS carried out arrests.

1542
01:51:17.924 --> 01:51:20.841
They handled the transportation of people
to the concentration camps.

1543
01:51:20.924 --> 01:51:22.966
Can you not recall a time

1544
01:51:23.049 --> 01:51:24.799
when the SS began to perform the function

1545
01:51:24.882 --> 01:51:27.424
of acting as the executor
of the Nazi Party?

1546
01:51:27.507 --> 01:51:30.549
It would be very difficult for me
to explain to an outsider

1547
01:51:30.632 --> 01:51:34.008
where the SS or where the <i>Gestapo</i>
may or may not be active.

1548
01:51:35.382 --> 01:51:36.382
Try.

1549
01:51:37.174 --> 01:51:41.966
Well. perhaps. as the police came more
and more into the hands of Himmler.

1550
01:51:42.507 --> 01:51:44.008
expectations may have changed.

1551
01:51:44.091 --> 01:51:47.174
And. of course. it is well-known
that some SS units

1552
01:51:47.258 --> 01:51:51.882
were guarding the camps. and later.
performed some police functions.

1553
01:51:53.008 --> 01:51:57.216
And carried out other functions
in the camps?

1554
01:51:58.008 --> 01:51:59.841
To what functions do you refer?

1555
01:52:01.507 --> 01:52:06.091
They carried out all of the functions
of the camps. didn't they?

1556
01:52:11.841 --> 01:52:14.882
If an SS unit was guarding a camp

1557
01:52:16.174 --> 01:52:19.507
and an SS leader was the camp commandant.

1558
01:52:20.841 --> 01:52:23.216
then it is rational to assume

1559
01:52:24.216 --> 01:52:28.841
that they would have carried out
all of the functions of the camp.

1560
01:52:30.049 --> 01:52:31.049
Bury him.

1561
01:52:31.133 --> 01:52:34.424
You have said that you wanted
a strong German State

1562
01:52:34.507 --> 01:52:37.340
to overcome the conditions of Versailles.
is that correct?

1563
01:52:37.424 --> 01:52:41.091
We wanted a strong German State.
regardless of Versailles.

1564
01:52:41.174 --> 01:52:43.924
The first country to be absorbed
by Germany was Austria

1565
01:52:44.008 --> 01:52:47.549
but it had not been part of Germany
before the First World War

1566
01:52:47.632 --> 01:52:49.382
and it had not been taken from Germany

1567
01:52:49.465 --> 01:52:51.049
by the Treaty of Versailles.
is that correct?

1568
01:52:51.133 --> 01:52:53.133
That is not entirely correct. no.

1569
01:52:53.216 --> 01:52:56.258
The second territory taken
by Germany was Bohemia.

1570
01:52:56.340 --> 01:52:58.300
<i>then Moravia. and then Slovakia.</i>

1571
01:52:59.632 --> 01:53:03.382
These were not taken from Germany
by the Treaty of Versailles

1572
01:53:03.465 --> 01:53:07.424
nor had they been part of Germany
before the First World War. had they?

1573
01:53:07.507 --> 01:53:09.757
These parts of Czech territory

1574
01:53:09.841 --> 01:53:15.258
were not parts of the smaller German Reich
at the time of the Treaty of Versailles.

1575
01:53:15.340 --> 01:53:16.632
However. formerly.

1576
01:53:17.300 --> 01:53:20.008
they were united to the German Reich...

1577
01:53:21.632 --> 01:53:23.174
for hundreds of years.

1578
01:53:23.258 --> 01:53:25.216
You still have not answered my question.

1579
01:53:25.300 --> 01:53:26.632
I have answered your question.

1580
01:53:26.716 --> 01:53:30.340
If the facts do not suit you.
there's very little I can do.

1581
01:53:30.424 --> 01:53:32.049
Can you not answer "yes" or "no"?

1582
01:53:32.133 --> 01:53:36.382
Time may not mean quite as much to you
as it does to the rest of us.

1583
01:53:36.465 --> 01:53:39.674
Mr. Justice. the Tribunal thinks
the witness ought to be allowed

1584
01:53:39.757 --> 01:53:43.382
to make what explanations he thinks right.

1585
01:53:43.966 --> 01:53:47.465
I trust that the Court is not unaware
that outside of this courtroom

1586
01:53:47.549 --> 01:53:50.757
is a great social question
regarding the revival of Nazism.

1587
01:53:50.841 --> 01:53:52.300
<i>and that one of the purposes</i>

1588
01:53:52.382 --> 01:53:53.674
<i>of defendant Göring</i>

1589
01:53:53.757 --> 01:53:56.049
is to encourage and perpetuate it

1590
01:53:56.133 --> 01:53:59.133
by propaganda from this trial
now in process.

1591
01:53:59.216 --> 01:54:01.424
- Mr. Justice...
- This witness has adopted

1592
01:54:01.507 --> 01:54:04.049
in the witness box and the prisoner's dock

1593
01:54:04.133 --> 01:54:07.799
an arrogant and contemptuous attitude
towards this Tribunal

1594
01:54:07.883 --> 01:54:11.549
which is giving him
the opportunity of a trial.

1595
01:54:11.632 --> 01:54:13.008
which he never gave a living soul!

1596
01:54:13.091 --> 01:54:15.924
The ruling stands. Mr. Justice.

1597
01:54:21.757 --> 01:54:25.049
I must. of course.
bow to the ruling of the Tribunal.

1598
01:54:26.424 --> 01:54:31.216
and would simply request that the witness
find a way to keep his answers succinct.

1599
01:54:35.258 --> 01:54:37.799
Could you please repeat the question?

1600
01:54:39.466 --> 01:54:42.841
They were not taken from you

1601
01:54:43.507 --> 01:54:46.549
-by the Treaty of Versailles. were they?
-Of course.

1602
01:54:46.632 --> 01:54:49.382
Austria was taken
by the Versailles Treaty.

1603
01:54:49.466 --> 01:54:50.799
and was too Sudetenland.

1604
01:54:52.924 --> 01:54:56.757
For both these territories
would have been German territories

1605
01:54:56.841 --> 01:54:58.757
through the simple right of the people

1606
01:54:58.841 --> 01:55:00.799
to self-determination.

1607
01:55:02.091 --> 01:55:03.466
Now. I find that interesting

1608
01:55:04.424 --> 01:55:07.424
considering you just testified
that people's self-determination

1609
01:55:07.507 --> 01:55:09.549
was the first thing you took away.

1610
01:55:11.924 --> 01:55:13.632
From the very beginning.

1611
01:55:13.716 --> 01:55:18.674
you regarded the elimination of Jews
from the economic life of Germany

1612
01:55:18.758 --> 01:55:23.674
as one phase of the Four-Year Plan
under your jurisdiction. is that correct?

1613
01:55:23.758 --> 01:55:25.841
- Partially correct.
- "Partially."

1614
01:55:26.632 --> 01:55:27.632
I see.

1615
01:55:28.382 --> 01:55:32.091
I would like to review with you briefly.

1616
01:55:32.966 --> 01:55:36.674
public acts taken by you
in reference to the Jewish question.

1617
01:55:37.300 --> 01:55:40.258
First. did you proclaim
the Nuremberg Laws?

1618
01:55:42.924 --> 01:55:44.466
Yeah. I did.

1619
01:55:44.549 --> 01:55:47.300
As President of the <i>Reichstag.</i>
that was my job.

1620
01:55:48.091 --> 01:55:49.216
What date was that?

1621
01:55:50.549 --> 01:55:52.758
15th of September. 1935.

1622
01:55:52.841 --> 01:55:56.300
Then on the first day of December 1936.

1623
01:55:56.382 --> 01:55:59.300
you passed an act
making it a death penalty for Germans

1624
01:55:59.382 --> 01:56:01.091
to transfer property abroad?

1625
01:56:01.924 --> 01:56:03.008
That is correct.

1626
01:56:03.091 --> 01:56:06.175
That was the "Decree Governing Restriction
on Foreign Currency."

1627
01:56:06.258 --> 01:56:09.133
Then. on April 22. 1938.
you published penalties

1628
01:56:09.216 --> 01:56:12.966
for concealing the character
of a Jewish enterprise within the Reich.

1629
01:56:13.050 --> 01:56:14.591
"Concealing." yeah.

1630
01:56:14.674 --> 01:56:17.382
Then. on April 26. 1938.
you signed a decree

1631
01:56:17.466 --> 01:56:21.632
ordering the registration of all Jewish
property inside and outside of Germany.

1632
01:56:22.966 --> 01:56:26.507
-If it is signed by me...
-Then a decree on November 12. 1938.

1633
01:56:26.591 --> 01:56:31.341
imposing a fine of one billion Reichsmarks
for atonement on all Jews.

1634
01:56:31.424 --> 01:56:33.300
- Yeah. but that is...
- And that all damages

1635
01:56:33.382 --> 01:56:36.549
caused to Jewish property
by the riots of 1938

1636
01:56:36.632 --> 01:56:40.382
must be repaired by Jews immediately
at their own expense.

1637
01:56:40.466 --> 01:56:42.632
and their insurance claims
forfeited to the Reich.

1638
01:56:42.716 --> 01:56:44.341
There are many details here.

1639
01:56:44.424 --> 01:56:46.424
- The insurance...
- And a decree

1640
01:56:46.507 --> 01:56:48.341
on the 17th of September. 1940.

1641
01:56:48.424 --> 01:56:51.133
ordering the sequestration
of all Jewish property in Poland.

1642
01:56:51.216 --> 01:56:55.300
Yeah. In that part of Poland.
it was a former German province

1643
01:56:55.382 --> 01:56:58.632
-And on July 31. 1941...
-...and would return to Germany.

1644
01:56:58.716 --> 01:57:01.258
...a decree asking Himmler and Heydrich

1645
01:57:02.175 --> 01:57:05.799
to make plans for the Final Solution
of the Jewish question.

1646
01:57:13.133 --> 01:57:14.133
That is not correct.

1647
01:57:14.883 --> 01:57:16.341
I know that decree very well.

1648
01:57:17.674 --> 01:57:20.633
I ask to have you shown Document 710.

1649
01:57:21.424 --> 01:57:23.216
exhibit number USA-509.

1650
01:57:26.050 --> 01:57:27.716
I think it should be read into the record

1651
01:57:27.799 --> 01:57:30.424
so we may have no argument
about its translation.

1652
01:57:30.507 --> 01:57:31.549
<i>Danke schön.</i>

1653
01:57:36.841 --> 01:57:39.674
That document
is signed by you. is it not?

1654
01:57:41.674 --> 01:57:42.716
That is correct.

1655
01:57:43.466 --> 01:57:45.466
Please correct me if I am wrong.

1656
01:57:48.175 --> 01:57:52.008
"Supplementing the task
that was assigned to you on 1-24-1939

1657
01:57:52.925 --> 01:57:54.341
"which dealt with arriving at...

1658
01:57:55.424 --> 01:57:58.799
"through furtherance of emigration
and evacuation

1659
01:57:58.883 --> 01:58:02.758
"a solution of the Jewish problem.
as advantageous as possible.

1660
01:58:02.841 --> 01:58:06.716
"I hereby charge you with making
all necessary preparations

1661
01:58:06.799 --> 01:58:08.216
"in regards to organizational

1662
01:58:08.300 --> 01:58:10.966
"and financial matters
for bringing about...

1663
01:58:12.507 --> 01:58:15.841
"a final solution of the Jewish question."

1664
01:58:16.966 --> 01:58:18.008
He's got him.

1665
01:58:21.424 --> 01:58:22.758
Am I correct so far?

1666
01:58:24.925 --> 01:58:27.591
No. Your translation is not correct.

1667
01:58:30.549 --> 01:58:32.883
Then. please. give us your translation.

1668
01:58:37.883 --> 01:58:42.258
"Supplementing the task
which was entrusted to you

1669
01:58:43.300 --> 01:58:46.507
"in the decree dated January 24. 1939.

1670
01:58:46.591 --> 01:58:50.091
"to solve the Jewish question
by emigration and evacuation

1671
01:58:50.175 --> 01:58:52.883
"in the most favorable way possible.

1672
01:58:55.091 --> 01:58:58.133
"Given present conditions.
I herewith commission you

1673
01:58:58.217 --> 01:59:01.008
"to carry out all necessary preparations

1674
01:59:01.091 --> 01:59:05.507
"with regard to organizational.
substantive. and financial viewpoints."

1675
01:59:06.758 --> 01:59:08.008
Now. here is...

1676
01:59:09.258 --> 01:59:10.633
the sentence.

1677
01:59:10.716 --> 01:59:14.175
"For a complete solution."

1678
01:59:14.258 --> 01:59:15.382
not "a final solution."

1679
01:59:16.300 --> 01:59:19.508
"For a total solution
of the Jewish question."

1680
01:59:22.300 --> 01:59:25.382
"A complete and total solution"?

1681
01:59:25.466 --> 01:59:27.674
Complete and total. yeah.

1682
01:59:27.758 --> 01:59:32.799
A complete and total solution
you wanted the Chief of the SS to enact?

1683
01:59:33.841 --> 01:59:37.008
Yeah. but I would like to make
an explanation.

1684
01:59:37.549 --> 01:59:38.633
Oh. please do.

1685
01:59:41.508 --> 01:59:45.508
I sent this letter
to Himmler and to Heydrich

1686
01:59:46.633 --> 01:59:49.549
because it was some 18 months now

1687
01:59:49.633 --> 01:59:53.050
since the declaration
of 24th of January. 1939.

1688
01:59:53.133 --> 01:59:55.341
And Heydrich had achieved very little.

1689
01:59:56.217 --> 01:59:58.674
so. I charged him to accelerate the task

1690
01:59:58.758 --> 02:00:00.966
of dealing with the emigration
of the Jews.

1691
02:00:04.008 --> 02:00:07.674
"Emigration"? You contend
this letter was about emigration?

1692
02:00:09.133 --> 02:00:11.382
It says so in the first line.

1693
02:00:20.883 --> 02:00:22.758
That's just the first sentence.

1694
02:00:22.841 --> 02:00:24.300
The letter goes on to state...

1695
02:00:24.382 --> 02:00:25.591
My desire...

1696
02:00:26.633 --> 02:00:29.091
for a complete solution
to the Jewish problem.

1697
02:00:29.841 --> 02:00:32.758
and an end to their financial influence

1698
02:00:32.841 --> 02:00:35.800
by their emigration and evacuation
from Germany.

1699
02:00:38.300 --> 02:00:41.716
It is in this document
that you presented to me.

1700
02:00:52.674 --> 02:00:55.258
Do you have
any more questions for the witness.

1701
02:00:55.341 --> 02:00:56.382
Justice Jackson?

1702
02:01:04.674 --> 02:01:07.800
Mr. Justice. is the witness excused?

1703
02:01:15.092 --> 02:01:16.549
I have a question.

1704
02:01:22.424 --> 02:01:24.841
Uh. the Tribunal was under the impression

1705
02:01:24.925 --> 02:01:28.925
the American prosecutor would be examining
this witness today.

1706
02:01:30.092 --> 02:01:32.633
Uh. the United States
is always happy to hear

1707
02:01:32.716 --> 02:01:35.466
from our distinguished colleague
from Great Britain.

1708
02:01:43.841 --> 02:01:45.716
Just a few simple queries.
Your Honors.

1709
02:01:45.800 --> 02:01:47.217
Won't take more than a moment.

1710
02:01:48.466 --> 02:01:52.175
You've implied to this Court
that you lost some influence

1711
02:01:52.258 --> 02:01:54.716
with Adolf Hitler in 1942.
is that correct?

1712
02:01:55.674 --> 02:01:58.383
I believe this to be the case. yeah.

1713
02:01:58.466 --> 02:02:02.300
But you were still
<i>Reichsmarschall</i> of Germany in 1942.

1714
02:02:02.925 --> 02:02:04.966
Hitler's successor. yes?

1715
02:02:07.258 --> 02:02:09.424
Yeah. I was the <i>Reichsmarschall.</i>

1716
02:02:10.633 --> 02:02:13.341
And you're telling me
that you were totally unaware

1717
02:02:13.424 --> 02:02:17.050
three million Jews were murdered in 1942?

1718
02:02:22.133 --> 02:02:23.633
I was unaware of this.

1719
02:02:23.716 --> 02:02:28.092
In 1943. at least 800.000 Jews

1720
02:02:28.175 --> 02:02:29.508
were executed in the camps.

1721
02:02:29.591 --> 02:02:33.383
You were still <i>Reichsmarschall</i> in 1943.
is that correct?

1722
02:02:35.050 --> 02:02:36.383
- That is correct.
- Hmm.

1723
02:02:36.466 --> 02:02:42.050
In 1944. an additional 800.000 Jews
died in the camps.

1724
02:02:42.133 --> 02:02:45.466
You were still <i>Reichsmarschall</i> in 1944.
is that correct?

1725
02:02:46.883 --> 02:02:47.925
That is correct.

1726
02:02:48.008 --> 02:02:52.675
In 1945. 250.000.

1727
02:02:52.758 --> 02:02:56.050
an estimated six million Jews in total.

1728
02:02:56.133 --> 02:02:58.967
as well as Soviet and Polish citizens.

1729
02:02:59.050 --> 02:03:02.341
Romani people. artists. scientists.

1730
02:03:02.424 --> 02:03:05.341
writers. journalists.
photographers. filmmakers.

1731
02:03:05.424 --> 02:03:08.092
people killed. not in combat.

1732
02:03:08.175 --> 02:03:10.092
not in enemy fire.

1733
02:03:10.175 --> 02:03:12.925
but exterminated by the state of Germany.

1734
02:03:13.008 --> 02:03:17.092
the State which you
were the <i>Reichsmarschall</i> of.

1735
02:03:17.175 --> 02:03:19.591
the pre-eminent political post
of your country.

1736
02:03:20.716 --> 02:03:24.967
and you contend that you had no knowledge.

1737
02:03:30.508 --> 02:03:31.841
At least give me this.

1738
02:03:33.259 --> 02:03:34.925
Knowing what we know now.

1739
02:03:36.008 --> 02:03:40.549
knowing what happened to six million Jews.
I have to ask...

1740
02:03:44.758 --> 02:03:48.925
Would you still follow
the <i>Führer.</i> Adolf Hitler?

1741
02:03:58.424 --> 02:03:59.424
Yeah...

1742
02:04:01.341 --> 02:04:02.341
I would.

1743
02:04:06.341 --> 02:04:07.967
Order! Order!

1744
02:04:11.758 --> 02:04:12.758
<i>Heil Hitler.</i>

1745
02:04:15.633 --> 02:04:16.800
No further questions.

1746
02:04:24.550 --> 02:04:26.800
I think
this as good a place as any

1747
02:04:26.883 --> 02:04:29.424
to adjourn for the day.

1748
02:04:35.800 --> 02:04:37.092
Fought brilliant.

1749
02:04:37.175 --> 02:04:38.175
Absolutely brilliant.

1750
02:04:40.383 --> 02:04:41.883
-I survived.
-You did it.

1751
02:05:07.675 --> 02:05:08.842
You were right.

1752
02:05:11.008 --> 02:05:12.217
I couldn't beat him.

1753
02:05:13.050 --> 02:05:14.259
Not without help.

1754
02:05:15.259 --> 02:05:17.217
"Göring cannot stand against the <i>Führer."</i>

1755
02:05:17.300 --> 02:05:19.217
- Invaluable information. Doctor.
- Hmm.

1756
02:05:22.591 --> 02:05:23.591
So. what now?

1757
02:05:25.508 --> 02:05:27.675
As Göring falls. so do they all.

1758
02:05:29.008 --> 02:05:30.008
We'll be okay.

1759
02:05:30.925 --> 02:05:31.925
Here.

1760
02:05:36.175 --> 02:05:37.300
You off?

1761
02:05:38.758 --> 02:05:40.591
Uh. one more thing I have to do.

1762
02:06:00.800 --> 02:06:02.008
<i>Doktor.</i>

1763
02:06:05.134 --> 02:06:06.800
You helped them. didn't you?

1764
02:06:08.050 --> 02:06:09.050
I did.

1765
02:06:11.383 --> 02:06:12.383
I'm leaving.

1766
02:06:14.175 --> 02:06:15.175
Leaving?

1767
02:06:17.383 --> 02:06:18.383
Going home.

1768
02:06:20.466 --> 02:06:21.967
I've come to say goodbye.

1769
02:06:26.217 --> 02:06:27.758
What do we do now. Doctor?

1770
02:06:29.842 --> 02:06:31.008
Do we shake hands?

1771
02:06:35.925 --> 02:06:38.092
I know we were friends. Douglas...

1772
02:06:40.675 --> 02:06:41.675
for a while.

1773
02:06:51.259 --> 02:06:52.341
Goodbye. Hermann.

1774
02:06:59.175 --> 02:07:00.425
Years from now...

1775
02:07:02.466 --> 02:07:04.591
I wonder what you will say about us.

1776
02:07:05.883 --> 02:07:08.050
Will you even acknowledge we were human?

1777
02:07:27.675 --> 02:07:31.883
The judgement
of the International Military Tribunal

1778
02:07:31.967 --> 02:07:32.967
will now be read.

1779
02:07:34.259 --> 02:07:37.508
Each defendant will be addressed in turn.

1780
02:07:40.633 --> 02:07:42.175
Hermann Göring.

1781
02:07:43.508 --> 02:07:46.675
the evidence shows that. after Hitler.

1782
02:07:46.758 --> 02:07:50.758
you were the most prominent man
in the Nazi regime.

1783
02:07:53.175 --> 02:07:56.341
<i>Your guilt is unique in its enormity.</i>

1784
02:07:57.842 --> 02:08:00.800
<i>Your record discloses no excuses.</i>

1785
02:08:02.925 --> 02:08:06.591
The International Military Tribunal
sentences you

1786
02:08:07.633 --> 02:08:09.217
to death by hanging.

1787
02:08:21.050 --> 02:08:22.633
Rudolf Hess.

1788
02:08:23.675 --> 02:08:26.466
You are indicted on all four counts.

1789
02:08:28.425 --> 02:08:31.967
The executions are scheduled
for midnight tonight.

1790
02:08:33.092 --> 02:08:34.967
In order to maintain discipline.

1791
02:08:35.675 --> 02:08:40.591
the prisoners will not be informed
until 11:45 p.m.

1792
02:08:40.675 --> 02:08:44.466
when they will be awakened in their cells
and offered last rites.

1793
02:08:45.550 --> 02:08:50.301
At 8:00 p.m.. eight hand-picked
journalists will arrive at the prison.

1794
02:08:50.383 --> 02:08:54.175
<i>Two French. two British.
two American. two Russian.</i>

1795
02:08:55.592 --> 02:08:57.633
<i>Lights out is at 9:30.</i>

1796
02:08:57.717 --> 02:09:00.758
<i>which is when the doctor
will do his normal final rounds.</i>

1797
02:09:00.842 --> 02:09:05.383
<i>Any prisoner requesting a sleep aid
will be given a placebo with baking soda.</i>

1798
02:09:08.383 --> 02:09:09.925
<i>At ten o'clock.</i>

1799
02:09:10.009 --> 02:09:12.633
<i>we will bring the press
down to the gallows</i>

1800
02:09:12.717 --> 02:09:16.259
<i>where I will brief them
on the final preparations for tonight.</i>

1801
02:09:30.925 --> 02:09:31.925
<i>Nein.</i>

1802
02:10:04.508 --> 02:10:05.925
Abracadabra.

1803
02:10:10.341 --> 02:10:13.050
The prisoners will be brought in
one-by-one.

1804
02:10:13.842 --> 02:10:17.050
and given the opportunity
to speak their last words.

1805
02:10:17.134 --> 02:10:18.301
They will then...

1806
02:10:22.592 --> 02:10:23.592
Excuse me.

1807
02:10:28.466 --> 02:10:29.717
-Who is it?
-Göring. sir.

1808
02:10:29.800 --> 02:10:30.800
Shit.

1809
02:10:37.717 --> 02:10:40.341
No. no. No. No!

1810
02:10:40.425 --> 02:10:42.425
No. you son of a bitch!
You don't get to do this.

1811
02:10:42.508 --> 02:10:44.508
He's dead. sir. Cyanide.

1812
02:10:44.592 --> 02:10:45.675
God damn it!

1813
02:10:49.176 --> 02:10:50.967
Oh. you son of a bitch.

1814
02:10:55.717 --> 02:10:58.592
I'm sorry. sir.
but we have a decision to make.

1815
02:10:59.425 --> 02:11:02.508
We can either scrub the executions
for tonight or proceed.

1816
02:11:03.092 --> 02:11:04.675
Let's just get on with it.

1817
02:11:04.758 --> 02:11:08.092
Sir. Uh. Streicher's refusing
to put his clothes on.

1818
02:11:15.717 --> 02:11:17.592
- Let him go. Let him go!
- But. sir...

1819
02:11:32.592 --> 02:11:33.592
Julius.

1820
02:11:35.967 --> 02:11:36.967
Julius.

1821
02:11:49.134 --> 02:11:50.134
You...

1822
02:11:52.675 --> 02:11:54.259
You have been a friend.

1823
02:12:05.925 --> 02:12:07.301
Come on.

1824
02:12:09.301 --> 02:12:10.550
Let's do it together.

1825
02:12:11.800 --> 02:12:13.383
Come on.

1826
02:12:15.675 --> 02:12:16.759
Give me his shirt.

1827
02:13:14.425 --> 02:13:15.717
Ask him his name.

1828
02:13:16.383 --> 02:13:18.884
You know my name.

1829
02:13:18.967 --> 02:13:20.592
Any last words?

1830
02:13:21.259 --> 02:13:24.259
Purim Feast. 1946!

1831
02:14:06.592 --> 02:14:08.717
Shit.

1832
02:15:24.176 --> 02:15:25.425
Son of a bitch.

1833
02:15:30.467 --> 02:15:31.550
He escaped.

1834
02:15:46.717 --> 02:15:48.259
<i>I have to be honest.
Dr. Kelley.</i>

1835
02:15:48.342 --> 02:15:51.509
<i>I find some of the conclusions
in your book quite unbelievable.</i>

1836
02:15:52.342 --> 02:15:57.467
<i>You were dealing with the Nazis.
who you must admit are a unique people.</i>

1837
02:15:57.550 --> 02:15:59.051
<i>They are not a unique people.</i>

1838
02:15:59.134 --> 02:16:03.842
There are people like the Nazis
in every country in the world today.

1839
02:16:03.926 --> 02:16:06.425
- Not in America.
- Yes. in America!

1840
02:16:07.342 --> 02:16:10.134
Their personality patterns
are not obscure.

1841
02:16:10.218 --> 02:16:12.759
They are people who want to be in power.

1842
02:16:12.842 --> 02:16:14.800
And while you say they don't exist here.

1843
02:16:14.884 --> 02:16:18.675
I would say I'm quite certain
there are people in America

1844
02:16:18.758 --> 02:16:22.759
who would willingly climb over the corpses
of half the American public

1845
02:16:22.842 --> 02:16:25.341
if they knew they could gain control
of the other half.

1846
02:16:25.425 --> 02:16:26.508
Doctor. please.

1847
02:16:26.592 --> 02:16:28.675
They stoke hatred.

1848
02:16:30.050 --> 02:16:32.217
It's what Hitler and Göring did.

1849
02:16:32.301 --> 02:16:34.176
and it is textbook.

1850
02:16:35.009 --> 02:16:37.550
And if you think the next time it happens.

1851
02:16:37.634 --> 02:16:40.634
we're gonna recognize it because
they're wearing scary uniforms...

1852
02:16:42.926 --> 02:16:44.717
...you're out of your damn mind.

1853
02:16:50.634 --> 02:16:52.926
More with our panel when we return.

1854
02:16:56.592 --> 02:16:58.342
Yeah. uh-huh. Uh...

1855
02:16:58.424 --> 02:17:00.884
They're not gonna invite you
to stay for the next segment.

1856
02:17:02.425 --> 02:17:03.425
Let's go.

1857
02:17:05.634 --> 02:17:06.884
Hmm.

1858
02:17:12.967 --> 02:17:14.175
And just so you know...

1859
02:17:15.884 --> 02:17:19.550
trashing our country is probably not
the best way to sell your book.

1860
02:17:21.967 --> 02:17:22.967
Hmm.
